1
00:00:34,934 --> 00:00:38,062
The Thakur...?
- Welcome, sir. This way...

2
00:04:25,164 --> 00:04:28,434
I knew it the moment I received
your letter, Thakur...

3
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:30,561
that you wished to meet me.
I took the first available train.

4
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:34,440
I'm putting you to
some trouble, jailer.

5
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:37,637
Not at all, sir. Just name it...
whatever it be.

6
00:04:38,011 --> 00:04:41,242
I need two men.
- Two?

7
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:59,764
Do you recognise them?

8
00:04:59,932 --> 00:05:04,198
There's hardly a prison where
they have not been held, Thakur.

9
00:05:05,104 --> 00:05:08,096
This is Veeru.
And this is Jai.

10
00:05:08,775 --> 00:05:13,303
They're crooks, both of them.
Thieves of the first order.

11
00:05:14,047 --> 00:05:15,708
I know.

12
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:22,719
They're just what I need
for the assignment at hand.

13
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:27,115
I can't say what assignment
you have in mind, Thakur.

14
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:30,752
But I can surely tell you that
they're good for nothing.

15
00:05:31,297 --> 00:05:33,322
That's not true, jailer.

16
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:40,066
For all their vices, they
have some virtues, too.

17
00:05:40,973 --> 00:05:43,874
A fake coin is a fake, sir.
Whichever way you look at it.

18
00:05:44,944 --> 00:05:48,004
That is perhaps the difference
between man and coin.

19
00:05:50,149 --> 00:05:54,210
I clearly remember what
happened two years ago.

20
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:58,919
I had arrested both of them
in district Jamalpur.

21
00:06:00,259 --> 00:06:03,922
We had to reach the police station
at village Tamli by dusk.

22
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:07,363
Since no other arrangements
could be made...

23
00:06:08,468 --> 00:06:10,936
we took a goods-train.

24
00:06:12,004 --> 00:06:15,940
I had two constables with me.
And there were these crooks...

25
00:06:16,142 --> 00:06:19,407
Jaidev and Veeru;
chained and handcuffed.

26
00:06:20,813 --> 00:06:24,271
Could you have been at the
Daulatpur police station earlier, sir?

27
00:06:24,917 --> 00:06:27,715
Yes, I was. Why did you ask?

28
00:06:28,321 --> 00:06:30,255
I remember now!

29
00:06:30,723 --> 00:06:33,920
I've been wondering where I've
seen you, ever since you've caught us.

30
00:06:34,293 --> 00:06:37,023
Remember Lalji's shop? The
provision store which we robbed?

31
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:41,697
Do you remember?
- The provision store? No...

32
00:06:42,001 --> 00:06:44,970
Don't you? Jai...

33
00:06:45,338 --> 00:06:48,398
Remember, we were held at
the Daulatpur police station?

34
00:06:49,041 --> 00:06:51,066
Daulatpur?
- Yes, don't you remember?

35
00:06:51,377 --> 00:06:55,313
When was that?
- We had robbed the grocer...

36
00:06:55,982 --> 00:06:59,748
He was the officer then...
Don't you recognise him?

37
00:07:00,787 --> 00:07:03,779
All police officers
look the same to me.

38
00:07:05,758 --> 00:07:09,319
I can't help it, you know...
He's always talking nonsense.

39
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:14,958
Since when have the two of you
been in this racket?

40
00:07:15,501 --> 00:07:20,131
You could say, we stood our own
two feet, the moment we could!

41
00:07:20,473 --> 00:07:22,270
But why must you do all this?

42
00:07:22,475 --> 00:07:25,342
The reason what you're a cop for...
we into it for the money.

43
00:07:25,845 --> 00:07:30,339
Not true. I'm not a police officer
just for the money.

44
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:34,276
I have enough of family land
to keep us going.

45
00:07:35,388 --> 00:07:39,051
But perhaps I'm fond of the
dangers involved in the game.

46
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:42,356
We face dangers everyday, too.

47
00:07:42,895 --> 00:07:47,958
There's a difference. I take on
dangers to protect the law.

48
00:07:48,401 --> 00:07:51,063
And you do it to
break the law.

49
00:07:51,838 --> 00:07:55,205
You need to be a brave man,
in both the cases.

50
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:56,940
Oh sure! You do need courage.

51
00:07:58,344 --> 00:07:59,811
I see.

52
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,074
You guys think you're
very brave, don't you?

53
00:08:03,249 --> 00:08:06,446
You will see when
the need arises, Inspector.

54
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:09,477
We'd atleast take on
15 or 20 guys.

55
00:08:09,956 --> 00:08:12,322
I haven't exaggerated it,
have I?

56
00:08:12,525 --> 00:08:15,358
Now that you've already said it...
- We deal with it!

57
00:08:26,906 --> 00:08:28,134
Bandits!

58
00:08:43,289 --> 00:08:45,416
Well, Inspector?
Want to try out our guts?

59
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:54,298
There's still time, Inspector.
Give it a thought!

60
00:09:04,510 --> 00:09:07,001
Don't you try to escape.

61
00:09:47,053 --> 00:09:48,680
Stop the engine, driver!

62
00:09:55,294 --> 00:09:58,593
Let's move ahead!
As fast as you can!

63
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:25,748
Charge ahead!

64
00:13:12,091 --> 00:13:14,025
Give me a swig! Quick!

65
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,912
Are you okay?
- I'm all right...

66
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:52,413
He dares mess with Veeru!

67
00:15:59,758 --> 00:16:01,157
They've fled, the swines!

68
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,585
Let's go... come on!

69
00:16:05,898 --> 00:16:09,561
I had warned you
not to escape...

70
00:16:19,178 --> 00:16:21,942
What do you think?
- We can run away.

71
00:16:23,682 --> 00:16:25,707
Leaving him in this state?

72
00:16:26,085 --> 00:16:28,645
He's going to die, if we
leave him in this condition.

73
00:16:29,722 --> 00:16:31,747
Suppose we take him
to the hospital...

74
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:34,256
we get sent away for
four or six months.

75
00:16:34,893 --> 00:16:37,885
So what do you suggest?
- What do you think?

76
00:16:39,031 --> 00:16:40,999
Get it out.

77
00:16:44,203 --> 00:16:48,071
If it's Heads, we go to the hospital;
if it's Tails, we escape.

78
00:16:57,216 --> 00:17:00,879
They are criminals, no doubt.
But they're terribly brave.

79
00:17:02,054 --> 00:17:05,820
They're dangerous, because
they know how to fight back.

80
00:17:06,959 --> 00:17:10,019
They're bad... but they're human.

81
00:17:12,297 --> 00:17:16,597
Could you find these
guys for me, jailer?

82
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:21,764
We'll easily find them, if they
are presently in some prison.

83
00:17:22,975 --> 00:17:26,342
But if they're free, it's
difficult to find such people.

84
00:18:12,458 --> 00:18:20,229
We Will Not Break This Friendship

85
00:18:20,666 --> 00:18:29,699
I May Break My Strength,
But I Will Not Leave Your Side

86
00:19:12,551 --> 00:19:17,623
Oh, My Victory Is Your Victory,
Your Loss Is My Loss

87
00:19:17,623 --> 00:19:20,956
Listen, Oh My Friend

88
00:19:21,693 --> 00:19:26,096
Your Pain Is My Pain,
My Life Is Your Life

89
00:19:26,231 --> 00:19:30,429
That Is How Our Love Is

90
00:19:30,536 --> 00:19:37,499
I Will Even Risk My Life,
For You I Will

91
00:19:43,048 --> 00:19:48,145
Become Enemies With Everyone

92
00:22:00,652 --> 00:22:05,324
People See Two Of Us, But

93
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:09,158
Look, We Are Not Two

94
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:13,899
Oh, That We Be Separated Or Angry,
Oh God I Pray

95
00:22:13,899 --> 00:22:17,562
That This May Not Happen

96
00:22:17,869 --> 00:22:21,828
We Will Eat And Drink Together

97
00:22:22,140 --> 00:22:25,439
We Will Die And Live Together

98
00:22:30,649 --> 00:22:34,050
For Our Entire Lives

99
00:23:58,036 --> 00:24:00,300
Soorma Bhopali! You're pulling
out more of the firewood.

100
00:24:00,505 --> 00:24:03,338
Naturally. You don't expect me
to put some more, do you?

101
00:24:03,975 --> 00:24:07,308
The scale says it's enough...
and you insist on more.

102
00:24:07,646 --> 00:24:10,114
Just take the wood and get going.
Give me the money...

103
00:24:10,449 --> 00:24:12,314
Here's a 2-Rupee bill.

104
00:24:12,651 --> 00:24:16,178
I can see that, but is it genuine?
Okay, it is.

105
00:24:18,023 --> 00:24:19,957
So then, good-bye.

106
00:24:21,026 --> 00:24:25,087
Won't you return my money?
- Money? What money do you want?

107
00:24:25,464 --> 00:24:28,228
That's a 2-Rupee bill!
- The wood is worth 2 Rupees too!

108
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:30,297
Just this much of wood
for two Rupees?!

109
00:24:30,435 --> 00:24:34,201
Were you out to buy the whole forest
for two bucks then?

110
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:38,307
Now look; I've had enough!
Just get going.

111
00:24:38,610 --> 00:24:42,478
I'm not Soorma Bhopali for nothing!
Okay?

112
00:24:42,747 --> 00:24:46,581
Get lost...
I wonder where they come from!

113
00:24:47,085 --> 00:24:50,486
He says the wood is too little!
Wants the forest then, does he?!

114
00:24:50,722 --> 00:24:53,247
They always come early every
morning to spoil my day!

115
00:24:53,658 --> 00:24:59,187
There, chand! You're at your
cursed poetry again!

116
00:24:59,531 --> 00:25:02,261
Go and check if they're unloaded
the stuff from the truck yet!

117
00:25:03,134 --> 00:25:05,625
Well! Well! Are you guys
watching a drama here?

118
00:25:06,371 --> 00:25:09,772
This is no travellers' bungalow...
who are you guys?

119
00:25:13,778 --> 00:25:16,508
God Almighty! It's you!

120
00:25:16,815 --> 00:25:22,048
How are you, Soorma Bhopali?
- I'm fine, thank you!

121
00:25:22,420 --> 00:25:25,150
But what are you guys up to?!

122
00:25:25,757 --> 00:25:27,190
Come here!

123
00:25:27,459 --> 00:25:32,226
The police have declared a reward
of 2000 Rupees for your arrest.

124
00:25:32,497 --> 00:25:34,658
If someone watches us together...

125
00:25:35,066 --> 00:25:39,162
I'll land in trouble, too!
So please get going!

126
00:25:39,471 --> 00:25:42,440
Know what, Soorma Bhopali?
We want to go to prison.

127
00:25:42,807 --> 00:25:45,037
I hope God fulfills your wish!

128
00:25:45,477 --> 00:25:49,106
Had this been Bhopal, I'd have had
you locked up in just two minutes!

129
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:52,346
I'm not Soorma Bhopali for
nothing, you know!

130
00:25:52,651 --> 00:25:54,380
But why would anyone
need me here?

131
00:25:54,719 --> 00:25:57,483
A warrant's out in
your name in any case!

132
00:25:57,822 --> 00:26:01,349
But we want you to
have us arrested.

133
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:03,625
What are you talking about?!

134
00:26:03,862 --> 00:26:07,559
There's a reward of 2000 Rupees
which you will get.

135
00:26:08,199 --> 00:26:13,796
Give us half the money, when
we're released from prison.

136
00:26:14,639 --> 00:26:17,267
Do you get it?
- What are you saying!

137
00:26:17,642 --> 00:26:23,410
Have some betel-leaf;
Go on... it's great!

138
00:26:32,657 --> 00:26:34,352
Since when have they started
having a parade here?

139
00:26:34,492 --> 00:26:38,223
You've just arrived, sonny boy.
You'll get to know soon.

140
00:26:38,563 --> 00:26:40,554
This new jailor is a nasty one!

141
00:26:40,865 --> 00:26:43,698
A nasty jailor, he says.
- There he is.

142
00:27:07,158 --> 00:27:09,183
Attention, I say!

143
00:27:09,728 --> 00:27:11,753
But they're already
at attention, sir.

144
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:17,461
I know that.

145
00:27:18,770 --> 00:27:22,297
Prisoners!
This is a warning for you!

146
00:27:23,208 --> 00:27:26,302
Everything that went unchecked
before my arrival here...

147
00:27:26,645 --> 00:27:28,670
will no longer be tolerated!

148
00:27:33,752 --> 00:27:37,347
I've been a jailor since
the British days!

149
00:27:37,622 --> 00:27:40,284
I don't belong to the breed
of jailors...

150
00:27:40,492 --> 00:27:43,393
who waste time, trying to
reform the prisoners!

151
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:49,596
I know it for a fact!
You guys can't be reformed!

152
00:27:50,535 --> 00:27:54,232
How can you ever change,
when I have not changed?

153
00:27:59,644 --> 00:28:03,375
I know, my words don't
go down well with you.

154
00:28:04,683 --> 00:28:09,245
Which is why I am transferred
from every place I work in.

155
00:28:11,256 --> 00:28:16,819
But despite all my transfers...
I have not changed!

156
00:28:19,397 --> 00:28:21,297
So you'd better remember!

157
00:28:21,566 --> 00:28:25,627
Don't think I am not informed
of all that you guys are up to!

158
00:28:26,905 --> 00:28:32,241
I have spies everywhere
in the prison.

159
00:28:32,944 --> 00:28:35,606
I get a report of every moment.

160
00:28:36,815 --> 00:28:41,548
Not even a bird could flap its
wings here without my consent!

161
00:28:42,620 --> 00:28:45,521
What the hell was that?!
- A bird... a pigeon, sir!

162
00:28:45,724 --> 00:28:48,284
What's that in my eyes...
never mind!

163
00:28:48,827 --> 00:28:52,763
This will do for today!
You may leave now.

164
00:28:57,702 --> 00:28:59,329
Let's go!

165
00:29:01,473 --> 00:29:03,338
Strange guy!

166
00:29:03,875 --> 00:29:06,002
Who could be the jailor's spy?

167
00:29:06,644 --> 00:29:10,239
I know that.
It's the barber, Hariram.

168
00:29:10,715 --> 00:29:14,310
He's very thick with the jailor.
The swine!

169
00:29:14,853 --> 00:29:16,445
Hariram, the barber?

170
00:29:23,328 --> 00:29:26,388
Go ahead and shave
my moustache, Hariram.

171
00:29:27,532 --> 00:29:29,830
It has all been arranged!

172
00:29:30,935 --> 00:29:32,926
We get cracking tomorrow.

173
00:29:33,705 --> 00:29:37,664
How many days will it take
to make the tunnel?

174
00:29:38,009 --> 00:29:39,874
You've cut my face!

175
00:29:40,512 --> 00:29:45,040
The tunnel? It should be
ready in about a week.

176
00:29:46,317 --> 00:29:48,751
Where are we going to
dig the tunnel from?

177
00:29:49,420 --> 00:29:52,321
It's from Barrack No. 9.

178
00:29:52,791 --> 00:29:55,316
I hope the jailor
doesn't get to know!

179
00:29:55,627 --> 00:29:58,528
No one will hear of it!

180
00:30:02,867 --> 00:30:04,596
Let's go!

181
00:30:06,604 --> 00:30:08,469
There. I'm through.

182
00:30:17,515 --> 00:30:19,949
Yes, Hariram?
What news do you bring?

183
00:30:20,618 --> 00:30:23,678
Be careful, sir. They're digging
a tunnel in the jail.

184
00:30:24,789 --> 00:30:27,815
Oh, well! A tunnel in my jail...

185
00:30:29,928 --> 00:30:31,953
What was that? A tunnel
in my jail?!

186
00:30:32,096 --> 00:30:34,030
Yes, sir. The prisoners are
making a tunnel in the jail.

187
00:30:35,099 --> 00:30:38,364
I've been a jailor since
the days of the British!

188
00:30:38,837 --> 00:30:42,864
A tunnel in my jail, eh?

189
00:31:09,734 --> 00:31:12,726
So this is where the
tunnel is being dug!

190
00:31:13,805 --> 00:31:15,670
This is wonderful!

191
00:31:16,007 --> 00:31:19,704
But you guys seem to have
forgotten that my spies...

192
00:31:20,578 --> 00:31:23,604
are spread out in
every part of the prison.

193
00:31:25,416 --> 00:31:27,441
And what is this?

194
00:31:32,190 --> 00:31:35,887
So this is the tool with which
you will dig the tunnel!

195
00:31:40,765 --> 00:31:43,996
I'm a jailor... from
the British days!

196
00:31:52,110 --> 00:31:54,101
Here he comes!

197
00:31:56,681 --> 00:31:59,115
Is it all arranged then?
- Yes.

198
00:31:59,784 --> 00:32:02,150
We won't miss out this time!

199
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:05,082
A pistol has arrived
in the prison!

200
00:32:05,490 --> 00:32:07,720
Has the pistol arrived?!

201
00:32:08,593 --> 00:32:17,001
In just a couple of days,
the jailor and his spies...

202
00:32:24,042 --> 00:32:26,067
A pistol in my prison, eh?

203
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:29,914
A pistol in my prison,
did you say?!

204
00:32:30,048 --> 00:32:31,777
A revolt?!
- That's right.

205
00:32:32,016 --> 00:32:33,881
Streams of blood?!
- Exactly.

206
00:32:43,594 --> 00:32:44,788
Halt!

207
00:32:45,763 --> 00:32:48,163
Search every nook and corner
of the jail!

208
00:32:48,833 --> 00:32:51,495
Half of you go in that direction.

209
00:32:52,603 --> 00:32:54,935
Half of you go there.

210
00:32:57,041 --> 00:33:00,977
The rest of you guys...
come with me!

211
00:34:10,581 --> 00:34:12,572
Here's the pistol!

212
00:34:13,684 --> 00:34:16,710
Move an inch, and...

213
00:34:18,790 --> 00:34:21,350
Guards!
- They've left.

214
00:34:24,162 --> 00:34:27,063
Let's go to your office.
- How can I?

215
00:34:27,532 --> 00:34:29,295
You have asked me not to move!

216
00:34:29,467 --> 00:34:32,231
The first order stands cancelled.
Let's go.

217
00:34:43,181 --> 00:34:47,481
Is the jailor of the British days
so scared?

218
00:34:49,687 --> 00:34:51,211
No!

219
00:34:52,557 --> 00:34:55,390
Come and see us off
at the gate first!

220
00:35:13,344 --> 00:35:15,369
Have the gate opened.

221
00:35:22,487 --> 00:35:24,318
Open the gate.

222
00:35:35,166 --> 00:35:37,134
Here's the key.

223
00:35:39,570 --> 00:35:41,595
And here's the "pistol"!

224
00:35:46,477 --> 00:35:48,843
The two of them must have
tried to run away, isn't it?

225
00:35:49,247 --> 00:35:51,613
Tried to run away?
That's an understatement!

226
00:35:51,916 --> 00:35:56,444
They put their lives into it!
But I wasn't about to let them go!

227
00:35:56,921 --> 00:36:01,153
As I held one of them,
the other tried to escape.

228
00:36:01,526 --> 00:36:05,292
I dragged him back and asked,
"Where to, feller?"

229
00:36:05,663 --> 00:36:08,723
With two stinging slaps, I ordered
them to the police station!

230
00:36:09,300 --> 00:36:11,700
That was it! They were
begging at my feet!

231
00:36:12,336 --> 00:36:14,361
Did Veeru and Jai really
beg at your feet?

232
00:36:14,639 --> 00:36:18,735
They're dangerous criminals!
- They're criminals, all right!

233
00:36:19,210 --> 00:36:23,442
But I'm not called Soorma
Bhopali for nothing!

234
00:36:23,881 --> 00:36:26,714
You can imagine!
They wept at my feet!

235
00:36:27,318 --> 00:36:30,776
And begged for forgiveness;
I'd have forgiven them, too!

236
00:36:31,355 --> 00:36:35,792
But I was furious that they had
dared to trespass my territory!

237
00:36:36,294 --> 00:36:38,285
What happened next?
- What else?!

238
00:36:38,596 --> 00:36:40,431
You know I carry a stick!

239
00:36:40,431 --> 00:36:43,923
It was days since I had used it.
So I got down to brass-tracks...

240
00:36:45,937 --> 00:36:48,167
and I really thrashed them!
I gave them a terrible beating!

241
00:36:48,439 --> 00:36:50,464
What happened next?
- What would have happened?

242
00:36:50,775 --> 00:36:55,303
I held them by their collars
and said...

243
00:36:55,780 --> 00:36:57,714
What did you say?
- What did I?!

244
00:36:57,915 --> 00:37:00,251
What did I say?!
Yes, I remember...

245
00:37:00,251 --> 00:37:03,914
I said, "Do let me know if there is
something more I can do for you"

246
00:37:04,689 --> 00:37:08,523
Well, guys... have you
nothing better to do?

247
00:37:08,826 --> 00:37:12,421
You plonk yourselves here and
compel me to concoct falsehoods!

248
00:37:12,630 --> 00:37:16,566
Go and attend to your work!
Go on... lazy bums!

249
00:37:18,402 --> 00:37:21,394
Well... I was only kidding.

250
00:37:21,772 --> 00:37:25,799
But you guys have been released
pretty quickly, haven't you?

251
00:37:26,377 --> 00:37:31,679
My word! The stint at the prison
seems to have been good for you!

252
00:37:34,018 --> 00:37:36,248
We are here to collect
our thousand Rupees.

253
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:39,787
A thousand rupees?
- That's right. A thousand bucks.

254
00:37:40,024 --> 00:37:41,787
I see!

255
00:37:42,360 --> 00:37:45,727
I got the money the very next day
of your arrest!

256
00:37:45,997 --> 00:37:51,401
Since that day, the money has been
lying in an envelope in my pocket!

257
00:37:51,602 --> 00:37:54,662
Check it out...
it's a thousand bucks!

258
00:37:55,573 --> 00:37:57,598
Well, Soorma... see you again.

259
00:38:09,820 --> 00:38:12,015
It's these chaps I've
been looking for.

260
00:38:12,523 --> 00:38:14,787
When does their prison term
come to an end?

261
00:38:15,826 --> 00:38:17,817
On the 18th of the next month.

262
00:38:23,901 --> 00:38:26,461
Could I have a beedi, guard?

263
00:38:43,521 --> 00:38:46,752
Well, Inspector? Whom have you
brought to the prison today?

264
00:38:47,925 --> 00:38:51,691
I'm not an Inspector anymore.
I'm just Thakur Baldev Singh.

265
00:38:52,697 --> 00:38:57,691
Why? Have you gotten over your
fondness of playing with dangers?

266
00:38:59,503 --> 00:39:03,371
If your bravery really makes
you so arrogant...

267
00:39:04,842 --> 00:39:06,867
will you accept
an assignment from me?

268
00:39:07,778 --> 00:39:10,611
We accept assignments
only for money.

269
00:39:11,582 --> 00:39:13,607
How much do you want?

270
00:39:17,621 --> 00:39:19,555
What's the job?

271
00:39:20,124 --> 00:39:23,389
Why must you worry about that,
if you're really brave?

272
00:39:23,994 --> 00:39:27,395
Name the price.
And you will get it.

273
00:39:28,432 --> 00:39:30,730
Provided you do what
I want you to do.

274
00:39:31,802 --> 00:39:35,738
Gabbar Singh?!
The notorious bandit?!

275
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:37,930
Yes. He's the one.

276
00:39:38,442 --> 00:39:40,808
The police are even said to have
placed a reward on his head.

277
00:39:41,078 --> 00:39:45,174
50,000 Rupees... for capturing him
dead or alive.

278
00:39:46,450 --> 00:39:50,181
You've got to capture the
bandit for me... alive.

279
00:39:51,155 --> 00:39:54,124
You want us to get Gabbar Singh...
that too, alive and kicking!

280
00:39:54,725 --> 00:39:58,661
Gabbar Singh is no sheep-kid
we could run and catch, Thakur!

281
00:39:59,497 --> 00:40:02,125
I know it's a difficult task.

282
00:40:03,134 --> 00:40:05,762
But no one pays so much
for something easy.

283
00:40:06,203 --> 00:40:10,435
Let's suppose we risk our lives and
somehow manage to capture him.

284
00:40:10,875 --> 00:40:14,208
Do you want us to hand him over
to you for just 20,000 Rupees?

285
00:40:14,612 --> 00:40:16,807
So you can make a cool
50,000 Rupees, for nothing?

286
00:40:17,715 --> 00:40:20,149
The reward from the police
will go to you, too.

287
00:40:20,551 --> 00:40:22,576
I only want Gabbar.

288
00:40:23,921 --> 00:40:25,946
Is it an old feud?

289
00:40:28,959 --> 00:40:31,120
That's none of your business.

290
00:40:35,266 --> 00:40:37,461
May I ask you another
question then?

291
00:40:37,868 --> 00:40:40,894
You know we're criminals, too.

292
00:40:42,006 --> 00:40:45,772
Why did you choose us
to track down the bandit?

293
00:40:46,143 --> 00:40:50,239
Only because iron
shall deal with iron.

294
00:40:57,054 --> 00:40:58,988
That's 5,000 Rupees.

295
00:40:59,256 --> 00:41:01,918
You will get 5,000 more upon
your arrival in Ramgarh.

296
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:05,620
The rest after you have
accomplished the mission.

297
00:41:12,002 --> 00:41:13,936
What do you suggest?

298
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:25,510
"Heads" -we go.

299
00:41:47,571 --> 00:41:49,539
Well, gentlemen?
Where will you go?

300
00:41:49,740 --> 00:41:52,800
Belapur, Rampur, Ramgarh...
where do you want to go?

301
00:41:54,245 --> 00:41:57,806
Have you never seen
a horse-cart before?

302
00:41:58,082 --> 00:41:59,709
This is a village, sir.

303
00:41:59,917 --> 00:42:03,683
You can't find cars here in
which you can speed away.

304
00:42:04,054 --> 00:42:06,079
Basanti's "tonga" is all
you will find around here.

305
00:42:06,290 --> 00:42:09,020
Now look; I'm not in the habit
of talking unnecessarily.

306
00:42:09,293 --> 00:42:12,126
Say so, if you wish to go...
- Well, we do wish...

307
00:42:12,329 --> 00:42:16,163
It's okay, if you don't wish to go!
You won't be my enemies!

308
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:19,567
I thought you'd need a tonga
and happened to ask you.

309
00:42:19,870 --> 00:42:22,065
But you don't have to be
my passengers, you know.

310
00:42:22,306 --> 00:42:24,240
It's your own free will!

311
00:42:24,642 --> 00:42:27,745
This is Basanti's tonga, not
the field of the landlord...

312
00:42:27,745 --> 00:42:29,770
which you will have to till,
even if you don't want to!

313
00:42:30,214 --> 00:42:33,809
This is just like...
- Let's go! We wish to go!

314
00:42:34,051 --> 00:42:37,043
Let's go!
- Sure. When have I refused?

315
00:42:37,321 --> 00:42:40,586
Now look; I'm not a chatter-box.

316
00:42:40,925 --> 00:42:43,257
So I'd better tell you in advance.

317
00:42:43,727 --> 00:42:46,093
A ride to Belapur costs 2 Rupees
and one to Rampur costs 1.5 Rupee.

318
00:42:46,363 --> 00:42:49,628
Don't haggle, please!
What Basanti says is final!

319
00:42:50,034 --> 00:42:52,832
Okay, but we...
- I know what you will say!

320
00:42:53,137 --> 00:42:56,766
Just why I charge 2 Rupees for
Belapur and 1.50 for Ramgarh?

321
00:42:56,907 --> 00:42:59,603
You'd better ask which village
this tonga belongs to. Go on.

322
00:43:01,045 --> 00:43:04,014
Well, where does it belong?
- It belongs to Ramgarh!

323
00:43:04,214 --> 00:43:07,342
I see! So it belongs
to Ramgarh! Now I know!

324
00:43:08,018 --> 00:43:09,315
Actually, there is this thing
worth considering.

325
00:43:09,820 --> 00:43:12,721
When I make a trip to Belapur,
I actually make two trips.

326
00:43:12,923 --> 00:43:14,652
To Belapur and back to Ramgarh.

327
00:43:14,992 --> 00:43:20,658
But should I go to Ramgarh,
it's like going home.

328
00:43:21,198 --> 00:43:24,827
Where would you like to go?

329
00:43:25,369 --> 00:43:27,360
Actually, we'd like
to go to Ramgarh, too.

330
00:43:27,805 --> 00:43:29,932
Sure! When have I refused?

331
00:43:30,741 --> 00:43:33,972
But you will have to tell me
whose house you're going to.

332
00:43:34,445 --> 00:43:36,675
So Basanti can take you
to that house.

333
00:43:36,947 --> 00:43:39,415
If l'm not told where
you've got to go...

334
00:43:39,817 --> 00:43:41,819
how will I stop the tonga?

335
00:43:41,819 --> 00:43:44,720
How will the tonga stop
if l don't stop it?

336
00:43:44,922 --> 00:43:49,882
Who holds the reins?
I do!

337
00:43:50,094 --> 00:43:51,391
And if l...

338
00:43:51,729 --> 00:43:54,425
We've got to go to Thakur
Baldev Singh's place.

339
00:43:56,100 --> 00:43:58,398
Sure! Let's go!
When did I refuse?

340
00:43:58,869 --> 00:44:00,666
You could said as much!

341
00:44:00,904 --> 00:44:02,735
Let's go, Dhanno!

342
00:44:10,881 --> 00:44:14,942
So you see, I had already
lost my parents.

343
00:44:15,386 --> 00:44:19,254
And who had to fend for my aunt
and ply the tonga?

344
00:44:19,723 --> 00:44:21,392
Me, of course.

345
00:44:21,392 --> 00:44:26,762
People ask how a girl like me
can go around plying a tonga.

346
00:44:27,231 --> 00:44:29,756
I have an answer ready
for them.

347
00:44:30,067 --> 00:44:32,900
Dhanno is a mare; and she
can still draw the cart.

348
00:44:33,170 --> 00:44:36,003
So why not Basanti?
Am I right?

349
00:44:36,306 --> 00:44:41,005
So what's wrong? City girls drive
cars... no one says anything to them.

350
00:44:42,212 --> 00:44:45,204
You're a wise man, although
you're from the city.

351
00:44:45,749 --> 00:44:48,115
What is your name?
- Veeru.

352
00:44:48,952 --> 00:44:51,477
You haven't yet asked me
my name, have you?

353
00:44:51,955 --> 00:44:53,855
What is your name, Basanti?

354
00:44:54,091 --> 00:44:56,924
Oh, shut up! You're always
talking nonsense!

355
00:44:57,294 --> 00:44:59,854
I wasn't talking to you, you know.

356
00:45:00,230 --> 00:45:03,427
But since you have asked me,
let me tell you...

357
00:45:03,801 --> 00:45:05,234
my name is Basanti.

358
00:45:05,402 --> 00:45:08,030
That's the first time
I've heard the name.

359
00:45:08,305 --> 00:45:11,069
Basanti! What a lovely name!

360
00:45:11,842 --> 00:45:15,471
There's a story
behind my name, too.

361
00:45:15,979 --> 00:45:17,844
Really? Do tell me...!

362
00:45:18,082 --> 00:45:20,880
When I was a little girl...

363
00:45:21,185 --> 00:45:24,211
a distant relative said...

364
00:45:41,105 --> 00:45:43,300
That's it, Dhanno! Halt!

365
00:45:43,874 --> 00:45:46,069
This is the Thakur's mansion.

366
00:45:47,177 --> 00:45:51,113
Strange! Talking to you guys,
I didn't even realise the distance.

367
00:45:51,315 --> 00:45:53,306
That's right.
We are very talkative.

368
00:45:53,550 --> 00:45:55,984
Here's the 1.50 Rupee
we had settled for.

369
00:45:56,353 --> 00:45:59,550
You're a nice man. I shouldn't be
accepting the money from you.

370
00:46:00,124 --> 00:46:03,184
But what will the horse eat,
if it befriends its food?

371
00:46:03,527 --> 00:46:07,156
So I will accept the money.
- That's very kind of you.

372
00:46:09,900 --> 00:46:11,492
Let's go, Dhanno!

373
00:46:19,476 --> 00:46:23,071
Wow! She talks so well!

374
00:46:23,981 --> 00:46:26,074
She talks too much!

375
00:46:26,450 --> 00:46:28,941
Let's go. You don't have to
score with every girl you meet.

376
00:46:29,153 --> 00:46:30,381
Come on!

377
00:46:33,457 --> 00:46:34,924
Welcome.

378
00:46:38,295 --> 00:46:39,489
This way, please.

379
00:46:44,501 --> 00:46:46,332
Greetings, Thakur.

380
00:46:46,570 --> 00:46:48,538
You had no problems
getting here, I hope?

381
00:46:49,206 --> 00:46:52,175
Well, not much.
- Come in.

382
00:46:55,579 --> 00:46:58,605
Had you dropped a letter, I'd have
sent someone to receive you.

383
00:47:00,184 --> 00:47:02,550
Your stay has been arranged.

384
00:47:03,020 --> 00:47:05,853
Just let me know, if there
is anything you need.

385
00:47:15,899 --> 00:47:19,130
I had promised to pay you 5000
rupees on your arrival here.

386
00:47:23,307 --> 00:47:26,902
You remember your
assignment, don't you?

387
00:47:28,345 --> 00:47:30,336
I want Gabbar.

388
00:47:30,948 --> 00:47:33,109
I want him alive.
- Of course, remember.

389
00:47:33,517 --> 00:47:37,385
You want Gabbar...
captured alive.

390
00:47:37,921 --> 00:47:39,411
You will have him.

391
00:47:40,958 --> 00:47:43,324
Go and take some rest.
You must be tired.

392
00:47:43,694 --> 00:47:46,094
We'll discuss the rest later.

393
00:47:46,430 --> 00:47:47,920
Follow me.

394
00:48:00,410 --> 00:48:03,277
Please go ahead.
I'll go and fetch the keys.

395
00:48:12,422 --> 00:48:15,050
That safe was
stuffed with riches!

396
00:48:16,293 --> 00:48:18,955
Folks in this village
seem to wear a lot of gold.

397
00:48:19,229 --> 00:48:21,254
So what do you say?

398
00:48:44,988 --> 00:48:49,357
Quite a big house...
and beautiful, too.

399
00:48:51,695 --> 00:48:54,459
Who else stays in there?
- Your keys.

400
00:48:56,033 --> 00:48:57,625
That is your quarters.

401
00:48:58,035 --> 00:49:00,060
Do call me over, should
you need something.

402
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:07,274
I can't quite figure this out.

403
00:49:07,577 --> 00:49:11,445
Why must we bother, Jai?
The Thakur has paid us 10,000.

404
00:49:12,215 --> 00:49:15,378
Let's clean out his safe tonight
and get away. What say?

405
00:49:16,653 --> 00:49:17,915
Very well.

406
00:49:19,256 --> 00:49:21,884
Let's sleep now, if we're going
to keep awake tonight.

407
00:50:59,689 --> 00:51:02,852
Thakur! These guys were...
- They're my men.

408
00:51:04,428 --> 00:51:06,020
Then why did they attack us?

409
00:51:06,563 --> 00:51:11,967
I wanted to see if you still
possess the courage and strength.

410
00:51:12,702 --> 00:51:17,833
Or whether time has rendered
your might, impotent.

411
00:51:18,809 --> 00:51:21,300
So? What did you see?

412
00:51:22,045 --> 00:51:29,417
I see that I have made no mistake
in having you brought here.

413
00:51:34,391 --> 00:51:36,985
There is one mistake you
have made, Thakur!

414
00:51:37,594 --> 00:51:40,324
You have shown us the
contents of your safe.

415
00:53:02,712 --> 00:53:04,737
Here's the key to the safe.

416
00:53:07,517 --> 00:53:10,918
The safe has some ornaments
which are of no use to me.

417
00:53:12,756 --> 00:53:15,054
A widow will never need them
again.

418
00:53:17,494 --> 00:53:20,930
It has some money, too.
You can take that away.

419
00:53:22,199 --> 00:53:26,659
I'm glad, it will atleast break
the Thakur's false hopes.

420
00:53:27,571 --> 00:53:29,766
Hopes, that he has pinned on you.

421
00:53:42,919 --> 00:53:43,908
Excuse me.

422
00:54:06,643 --> 00:54:09,168
That which happened last night
will not happen again.

423
00:54:29,933 --> 00:54:31,901
Here... have some more!

424
00:54:32,269 --> 00:54:34,260
You've eaten enough
to be big and strong!

425
00:54:34,804 --> 00:54:38,103
But when we make to trip to Belapur,
you sure do put on airs!

426
00:54:38,742 --> 00:54:42,234
Go ahead and eat...!
- Basanti...!

427
00:54:42,746 --> 00:54:45,544
I'm here, feeding
this donkey, aunty!

428
00:54:45,982 --> 00:54:48,212
Now watch her take off!

429
00:54:48,952 --> 00:54:52,786
Listen, lady!
You can roam around all day!

430
00:54:53,156 --> 00:54:55,886
But you wouldn't do
a simple chore for me!

431
00:54:56,192 --> 00:54:57,955
There she is! Ranting as usual!

432
00:54:58,128 --> 00:55:01,586
You're always losing
your temper with me, aunty.

433
00:55:01,831 --> 00:55:03,992
Won't you give me a chance?
What had you asked me to do?

434
00:55:04,234 --> 00:55:05,997
You asked me to go to
the physician, didn't you?

435
00:55:06,303 --> 00:55:09,033
I did go to him to
fetch your medicines.

436
00:55:09,339 --> 00:55:13,139
But he wasn't there.
He's supposed to be ill...

437
00:55:13,343 --> 00:55:15,868
and has gone to the neigbouring
village for treatment.

438
00:55:16,046 --> 00:55:19,846
I didn't mention the doctor and
you gave me a whole lecture!

439
00:55:20,183 --> 00:55:22,208
What else did you ask me to do?

440
00:55:22,652 --> 00:55:24,847
Didn't I ask you to fetch some
raw mangoes for the pickle?

441
00:55:25,055 --> 00:55:26,920
But you will never remember!

442
00:55:27,257 --> 00:55:30,988
Oh sure, you did tell me!
I'll go and fetch them right away!

443
00:55:33,930 --> 00:55:36,899
Imam Saheb! Do you want me
to reach you home?

444
00:55:37,267 --> 00:55:38,234
Who's that?

445
00:55:38,735 --> 00:55:41,966
Basanti! It's you today.

446
00:55:42,872 --> 00:55:46,968
I've spent years in this village.
You weren't even born then.

447
00:55:48,111 --> 00:55:51,638
But even before I can alight
the steps of the mosque...

448
00:55:52,182 --> 00:55:54,582
there is someone
to reach me home.

449
00:55:54,884 --> 00:55:56,681
Why wouldn't anyone?

450
00:55:56,886 --> 00:55:59,218
There's not a soul in town
who does not respect you.

451
00:55:59,689 --> 00:56:02,317
When they respect you so much,
why won't they help you too?

452
00:56:02,792 --> 00:56:05,352
It's all very natural.
Actually...

453
00:56:05,829 --> 00:56:09,162
When you can talk so much, why don't
you talk some sense to Ahmed too?

454
00:56:09,933 --> 00:56:11,768
He's even younger to you.

455
00:56:11,768 --> 00:56:14,828
I know how to make them
see sense, lmam.

456
00:56:15,105 --> 00:56:17,005
I can make your son
see reason too.

457
00:56:17,173 --> 00:56:23,339
But unless I know what I have
to talk about, how will I?

458
00:56:23,980 --> 00:56:28,246
Ahmed's uncle works for a beedi-
manufacturing factory in Jabalpur.

459
00:56:28,818 --> 00:56:31,218
He earns 300 Rupees every month!
- Really?

460
00:56:31,855 --> 00:56:34,688
He has written to me so very often
to send Ahmed over...

461
00:56:34,958 --> 00:56:37,620
so he'll talk to his boss and
find Ahmed a job in the same factory.

462
00:56:38,061 --> 00:56:40,086
But Ahmed is just not
prepared to go!

463
00:56:40,730 --> 00:56:42,755
He says I'd be left all alone!

464
00:56:43,733 --> 00:56:46,167
Hi! How are you?
- I'm fine, all right.

465
00:56:46,403 --> 00:56:50,635
Now tell me; you've completed your
matriculation and speak English too.

466
00:56:51,040 --> 00:56:53,235
And as your uncle
in Jabalpur writes...

467
00:56:53,443 --> 00:56:56,173
There you are! You're taken up
with my father says, too!

468
00:56:56,413 --> 00:56:58,176
That's the only thing he says
to anyone who meets him.

469
00:56:58,348 --> 00:57:00,373
So what's wrong? I just answered
a question she asked.

470
00:57:00,784 --> 00:57:03,753
You know, I'm not used
to talking without reason.

471
00:57:04,154 --> 00:57:06,956
But just think it over!
It's a beedi-manufacturing factory!

472
00:57:06,956 --> 00:57:09,925
Work while you work... and smoke
a beedi, when you feel like it!

473
00:57:10,059 --> 00:57:13,358
It's like getting all the
mangoes for nothing...

474
00:57:13,930 --> 00:57:16,296
My God!
- What's wrong?

475
00:57:16,900 --> 00:57:19,767
The mangoes! I forgot them again!

476
00:57:20,170 --> 00:57:21,831
The raw-mangoes!
- The raw mangoes?

477
00:57:22,038 --> 00:57:24,336
Yes. I had to fetch them
for the pickle...

478
00:57:46,463 --> 00:57:48,954
Well? What are you doing here?

479
00:57:49,332 --> 00:57:51,892
Well...! That's how it is.

480
00:57:53,002 --> 00:57:54,993
Well... which mango do you
want me to knock off?

481
00:57:55,238 --> 00:57:57,968
Can you really shoot down
the mango I want?

482
00:57:58,041 --> 00:58:00,134
That's child's play!

483
00:58:00,410 --> 00:58:02,970
The best of the big shots pay
respects at my meet...

484
00:58:03,179 --> 00:58:06,239
and swear they haven't seen
a marksman like me!

485
00:58:06,349 --> 00:58:08,317
You seem to be a damn good-shot!

486
00:58:08,485 --> 00:58:10,453
Sure... he's of royal
descent, isn't he?

487
00:58:11,120 --> 00:58:14,988
What was that he said?
- Never mind. He talks nonsense.

488
00:58:15,358 --> 00:58:17,223
So, which mango do you want?

489
00:58:19,162 --> 00:58:23,098
That one there... the other one,
too. And yet another one there.

490
00:58:35,945 --> 00:58:38,140
My word! Your friend
is a great shot, too!

491
00:58:38,348 --> 00:58:40,248
Eh? Oh, yes. Bright chap, you know.

492
00:58:40,416 --> 00:58:42,884
I'm still teaching him...
He'll learn soon.

493
00:58:43,186 --> 00:58:46,246
Can you teach me, too?
- Certainly! I can teach you, too!

494
00:58:46,489 --> 00:58:49,117
In fact, I can teach you this
in a matter of two days.

495
00:58:49,392 --> 00:58:51,417
In just two days?!
- Of course.

496
00:58:51,828 --> 00:58:54,353
There have been people he has
"taught" in a couple of hours!

497
00:58:58,034 --> 00:59:00,502
In just a couple of hours!
- He talks nonsense, you know!

498
00:59:00,970 --> 00:59:04,030
Well, come with me, if you
wish to learn this.

499
00:59:05,141 --> 00:59:07,132
Can you see that mango there?

500
00:59:07,477 --> 00:59:08,967
You can see it, can't you?
- Sure.

501
00:59:09,279 --> 00:59:11,270
Now hold the gun...

502
00:59:12,382 --> 00:59:17,115
and bring this other hand...
close to the other.

503
00:59:17,554 --> 00:59:21,251
Now place this finger
on the trigger.

504
00:59:21,958 --> 00:59:23,983
Now close your eye and...

505
00:59:24,294 --> 00:59:26,524
I have already shut my eyes!

506
00:59:28,031 --> 00:59:31,831
What is he talking about?
- The usual nonsense!

507
00:59:32,869 --> 00:59:35,497
Now close your eyes.
- Very well.

508
00:59:36,306 --> 00:59:39,139
Now... can you see that mango?

509
00:59:40,543 --> 00:59:44,570
Strange! How can I see the mango,
when I've shut my eyes?

510
00:59:45,148 --> 00:59:47,139
Have you shut both your eyes?!
- Yes.

511
00:59:47,383 --> 00:59:50,443
But you must shut only
your left eye... this one!

512
00:59:51,087 --> 00:59:53,578
Now use your other eye
to aim at the mango.

513
00:59:53,990 --> 00:59:57,187
Okay. And what do I do now?
- Now? Well...

514
00:59:57,460 --> 00:59:59,485
Now squeeze the trigger!

515
01:00:04,968 --> 01:00:06,230
He's found his mark!

516
01:00:08,004 --> 01:00:11,235
I thought I was learning
to handle a gun.

517
01:00:11,908 --> 01:00:14,342
But now I smell a rat!

518
01:00:15,044 --> 01:00:18,070
A rat? What is that?
I don't understand!

519
01:00:18,481 --> 01:00:20,073
But I understand this
perfectly well!

520
01:00:20,316 --> 01:00:24,582
You city-guys think we in the
countryside are morons!

521
01:00:25,188 --> 01:00:31,024
But Basanti could very well
teach you a lesson!

522
01:00:31,294 --> 01:00:35,287
I was only teaching you!
You're misunderstanding me!

523
01:00:35,665 --> 01:00:38,259
I understand you very well!

524
01:00:38,534 --> 01:00:41,867
Sit here with your gun!
I'm going home!

525
01:00:42,138 --> 01:00:43,469
Good-bye!

526
01:03:28,004 --> 01:03:32,703
Kashiram! Dholiya!
Where the hell are all of you?

527
01:03:39,282 --> 01:03:42,649
