716
01:33:12,787 --> 01:33:14,652
You're going to the station to
receive grandpa, aren't you?

717
01:33:15,256 --> 01:33:17,383
May I come along, too?
- Go and ask your mother.

718
01:33:17,658 --> 01:33:19,182
Why don't you tell her?

719
01:33:19,393 --> 01:33:23,329
Just tell her that you're
going with me. Go on.

720
01:33:25,366 --> 01:33:27,630
Mother...

721
01:33:28,202 --> 01:33:29,533
Let me cut the vegetables.

722
01:33:29,937 --> 01:33:32,167
May I go to the station
with uncle, mother?

723
01:33:32,373 --> 01:33:34,273
No. You're not going
to the station.

724
01:33:34,408 --> 01:33:35,776
Madam... I've asked someone
to fix the main-gate.

725
01:33:35,776 --> 01:33:38,336
Madam... I've asked someone
to fix the main-gate.

726
01:33:39,246 --> 01:33:45,412
And here are the things
you had asked for...

727
01:33:47,555 --> 01:33:51,150
Young mistress!
- I'm coming over!

728
01:34:00,167 --> 01:34:03,227
I'm going to the temple. But if
there is anything I can do...?

729
01:34:03,604 --> 01:34:05,299
Go on. I'll handle it.

730
01:34:05,506 --> 01:34:07,531
Let's go.
- Give me that.

731
01:34:11,445 --> 01:34:14,744
May I go to the station, mom?
- Haven't I said you can't?

732
01:34:15,516 --> 01:34:17,780
Let him go, if he wants to.

733
01:34:18,285 --> 01:34:21,652
No way. There are always so many
trains passing by. I'm scared.

734
01:34:21,956 --> 01:34:24,925
The trains seem to have an axe
to grind against your son.

735
01:34:25,593 --> 01:34:28,721
They'll leave their tracks
to go after him!

736
01:34:29,397 --> 01:34:31,695
You have a funny logic.

737
01:34:32,833 --> 01:34:35,597
So you're preparing the
vegetable father likes, eh?

738
01:34:35,903 --> 01:34:38,929
Let him go, I say.
- Okay! Go ahead and spoil him!

739
01:34:40,007 --> 01:34:42,771
Will you go like this?
Go and have a bath.

740
01:34:43,310 --> 01:34:44,679
Ask your aunt to... Nirmala!
- Yes, sister-in-law?

741
01:34:44,679 --> 01:34:47,341
Ask your aunt to... Nirmala!
- Yes, sister-in-law?

742
01:34:47,648 --> 01:34:49,673
Will you get a set of clothes
out for the kid, my girl?

743
01:34:49,850 --> 01:34:52,512
Right away.
- Go on.

744
01:34:53,354 --> 01:34:55,618
And you've started chewing
on the raw vegetables!

745
01:34:56,691 --> 01:34:59,990
They're all busy today
to impress father!

746
01:35:00,461 --> 01:35:03,487
As if you get the witch to
do the chores every day!

747
01:35:04,031 --> 01:35:06,864
This wheel is still lying here?

748
01:35:08,102 --> 01:35:11,697
Ramlal has become
a forgetful old man.

749
01:35:12,440 --> 01:35:16,900
I'd asked him to have the drawing
room and father's room cleaned.

750
01:35:17,445 --> 01:35:19,413
But he's not even to be seen.

751
01:35:19,680 --> 01:35:23,514
He's away at the temple with Radha.
He will do it when he returns.

752
01:35:23,918 --> 01:35:26,614
Hey, Ninni!
- Yes, brother?

753
01:35:26,921 --> 01:35:30,687
Have a bath and get ready!
Aren't we going to the station?

754
01:35:31,058 --> 01:35:33,083
I'll join you in a minute!

755
01:35:35,429 --> 01:35:40,025
I can't figure out how this silly
hunter found a wife like Radha.

756
01:35:41,068 --> 01:35:43,662
It was I who asked father
to pursue the alliance.

757
01:35:43,971 --> 01:35:46,462
But does anyone even
acknowledge what I've done?

758
01:35:46,741 --> 01:35:48,766
I've found him a wife
who's one in a million!

759
01:35:48,976 --> 01:35:53,504
Or girls nowadays ask for a division
the day they are married.

760
01:35:53,981 --> 01:35:57,041
Wait and see what a great match
I find for Nimmo next.

761
01:36:01,088 --> 01:36:02,077
No!

762
01:40:30,657 --> 01:40:32,147
Gabbar?

763
01:40:35,996 --> 01:40:37,327
Yes...

764
01:42:37,284 --> 01:42:39,184
Welcome, Thakur.

765
01:42:40,787 --> 01:42:43,483
I knew for sure
that you'd come here.

766
01:42:48,529 --> 01:42:50,759
The ass struggles!

767
01:42:51,398 --> 01:42:54,333
You contemptible bastard!
God-damn scoundrel!

768
01:42:56,303 --> 01:42:59,966
Curse me as much as you wish!
To your heart's content!

769
01:43:00,240 --> 01:43:03,971
You bastard!
- Yes! Shout some more!

770
01:43:04,811 --> 01:43:08,372
Remember? I cried the other day
and you watched the fun?

771
01:43:09,950 --> 01:43:11,218
You will cry your lungs out today...
and I will watch the fun!

772
01:43:11,218 --> 01:43:13,152
You will cry your lungs out today...
and I will watch the fun!

773
01:43:14,154 --> 01:43:15,917
Know what, Samba?

774
01:43:16,456 --> 01:43:21,792
I was livid at the court that
day... so very furious!

775
01:43:22,329 --> 01:43:25,389
I could have wrung his neck
there and then! The bastard!

776
01:43:26,233 --> 01:43:30,101
But I couldn't help it!
I was held by four of those cops!

777
01:43:30,604 --> 01:43:33,505
Handcuffs in my hands...
my legs shackled! Remember?

778
01:43:35,075 --> 01:43:36,975
You remember that, don't you?

779
01:43:41,615 --> 01:43:43,810
Any last wish, Thakur?

780
01:43:51,124 --> 01:43:54,093
There's still a lot
of life in your arms.

781
01:43:55,862 --> 01:43:57,431
Tie him up!

782
01:43:57,431 --> 01:43:57,897
Tie him up!

783
01:44:11,211 --> 01:44:13,236
I'm not going to kill you now.

784
01:44:14,615 --> 01:44:20,053
After I'm through with you...
the world will spit on you.

785
01:44:20,053 --> 01:44:20,246
After I'm through with you...
the world will spit on you.

786
01:44:21,955 --> 01:44:23,946
Your arms are full of life!

787
01:44:25,525 --> 01:44:29,325
His arms are strong enough
to pull down a running horse!

788
01:44:32,299 --> 01:44:34,859
Your arms are full of life!

789
01:44:35,502 --> 01:44:38,062
D'you remember what you
had once told me?

790
01:44:38,505 --> 01:44:41,565
They aren't arms...
they're a noose!

791
01:44:42,943 --> 01:44:43,210
And here you are!
The noose has been destroyed!

792
01:44:43,210 --> 01:44:46,236
And here you are!
The noose has been destroyed!

793
01:44:46,980 --> 01:44:49,005
It has been ripped open!

794
01:44:50,183 --> 01:44:52,447
Arms full of life, aren't they?

795
01:44:54,388 --> 01:44:56,288
These arms...

796
01:44:57,057 --> 01:44:59,389
give them to me, Thakur.
- No!

797
01:45:00,460 --> 01:45:04,226
Give me your arms, Thakur!
- No!

798
01:46:16,303 --> 01:46:18,828
Did you see anything else?
- No, sir.

799
01:46:19,906 --> 01:46:21,931
We shut our doors and windows
when we heard the gunfire.

800
01:46:22,142 --> 01:46:24,110
I see... very well.

801
01:46:25,078 --> 01:46:27,808
Put your thumb-impression here.
- Very well, sir.

802
01:46:30,417 --> 01:46:31,816
Welcome, Thakur.

803
01:46:35,088 --> 01:46:38,148
I've got to know of what happened
here, from these folks.

804
01:46:38,525 --> 01:46:40,117
I wanted to discuss
something with you.

805
01:46:40,894 --> 01:46:44,921
The police want Gabbar;
dead or alive.

806
01:46:47,033 --> 01:46:49,228
You will have him one day.

807
01:46:50,871 --> 01:46:53,499
Is there something you can
tell me about Gabbar?

808
01:46:54,274 --> 01:46:55,263
No.

809
01:46:56,343 --> 01:46:59,107
Okay. That's all I wanted to know.

810
01:46:59,546 --> 01:47:01,480
Thank you, Thakur.

811
01:47:05,852 --> 01:47:06,876
Good-bye.

812
01:47:20,300 --> 01:47:25,602
We don't want that money, Thakur.

813
01:47:26,506 --> 01:47:28,497
Please take it back.

814
01:47:29,242 --> 01:47:32,006
Please don't think, we won't carry
out the mission for you.

815
01:47:35,348 --> 01:47:40,115
But didn't you say
you only work for money?

816
01:47:40,520 --> 01:47:42,215
Well, we...

817
01:47:43,323 --> 01:47:45,621
We will get the money anyway.

818
01:47:47,394 --> 01:47:50,261
Once we have killed Gabbar...
- You will not kill Gabbar!

819
01:47:52,899 --> 01:47:57,927
You are here to catch Gabbar alive
and hand him over to me.

820
01:47:59,005 --> 01:48:03,066
Give me your word! That you will
hand him over to me, alive!

821
01:48:09,416 --> 01:48:15,116
We give you our word, Thakur.
But please take back the money.

822
01:48:18,992 --> 01:48:22,086
Girija, the blacksmith, brings
some news from village Titli.

823
01:48:25,265 --> 01:48:28,564
You might meet Gabbar
again very soon.

824
01:48:30,370 --> 01:48:31,337
Come on.

825
01:48:35,375 --> 01:48:37,366
Greetings, Thakur.
- Greetings.

826
01:48:38,144 --> 01:48:40,169
So what's news, Girija?

827
01:48:40,547 --> 01:48:43,072
There are some gypsies
staying at Pipri.

828
01:48:43,683 --> 01:48:46,379
Hira and his friends
are there too.

829
01:48:47,988 --> 01:48:51,048
Hira is the one who sells
arms and ammunition to Gabbar.

830
01:48:52,125 --> 01:48:55,185
Gabbar is bound to meet him
in a couple of days.

831
01:48:55,729 --> 01:48:59,324
Strike... when the iron is hot.

832
01:49:45,779 --> 01:49:48,111
Beloved, Oh Beloved

833
01:49:54,321 --> 01:49:56,289
Oh, Beloved, Oh Beloved

834
01:50:02,662 --> 01:50:05,532
Roses Blossom In Gardens

835
01:50:05,532 --> 01:50:08,433
When We Meet In The Desert

836
01:50:11,304 --> 01:50:14,603
Me And You

837
01:50:55,181 --> 01:50:57,342
A Flower Came Out From Spring,

838
01:50:59,419 --> 01:51:02,286
The Moon Came Out From The Stars

839
01:51:07,894 --> 01:51:10,260
The Daytime Has Drowned

840
01:51:53,440 --> 01:52:06,286
The The Road Of Beauty And Love,
In Your Arms And Eyes

841
01:52:06,286 --> 01:52:09,153
My Heart Has Drowned

842
01:53:55,662 --> 01:53:57,687
My God! What happened to him?

843
01:53:58,598 --> 01:54:01,658
Don't worry. The bullet has
just grazed his arm.

844
01:54:02,402 --> 01:54:04,427
It's not a serious injury.

845
01:54:05,939 --> 01:54:08,635
We blew up almost all their
arms and explosives, Thakur...

846
01:54:09,042 --> 01:54:11,272
but Gabbar managed to escape.

847
01:54:11,511 --> 01:54:14,503
It's okay. We'll get him
again someday.

848
01:54:19,652 --> 01:54:23,611
Take a swig, partner.
Your troubles will vanish.

849
01:54:24,757 --> 01:54:27,920
Should you stop drinking, it will
reduce most of your troubles.

850
01:54:29,295 --> 01:54:31,263
Would you like to...?
- God almighty!

851
01:54:55,889 --> 01:54:58,915
Greetings, lmam.
I have a letter for you.

852
01:54:59,759 --> 01:55:02,489
Here you are.
- It must be from Jabalpur.

853
01:55:03,329 --> 01:55:06,890
Could you read it for me?
- Certainly.

854
01:55:08,501 --> 01:55:10,737
Where are my glasses?
I put it in my pocket!

855
01:55:10,737 --> 01:55:14,673
That which you are looking for
is here with me!

856
01:55:14,874 --> 01:55:17,069
Here you are!
- The chatterbox is here, isn't she?

857
01:55:17,610 --> 01:55:21,376
Actually, we were going in
the opposite directions.

858
01:55:21,948 --> 01:55:23,973
You were on your bicycle
and I was on foot.

859
01:55:24,417 --> 01:55:27,545
You dropped your glasses
and I picked them up!

860
01:55:27,854 --> 01:55:30,482
I guessed as much that the
glasses must belong to you.

861
01:55:30,790 --> 01:55:33,782
The funny part is, it's
really yours. Actually...

862
01:55:33,993 --> 01:55:37,656
If you rest your mouth a little,
I'd know what the letter says.

863
01:55:37,864 --> 01:55:40,765
I'll listen to you later.
- Okay! When did I refuse?

864
01:55:41,034 --> 01:55:45,061
It begins with a greeting.
- Greetings himself, too.

865
01:55:46,039 --> 01:55:52,501
Everything is fine here and we
pray for your well-being.

866
01:55:53,479 --> 01:55:57,506
"The good news is that the job
for Ahmed has been finalised"

867
01:55:57,984 --> 01:56:00,009
"He will get a salary
of 200 Rupees"

868
01:56:00,720 --> 01:56:03,746
"He can very well stay with me
and eat with us, too"

869
01:56:03,957 --> 01:56:06,517
It's good that he will
be in his uncle's care.

870
01:56:06,893 --> 01:56:09,521
Oh yes! That's wonderful!
That's just what I wanted, too.

871
01:56:09,996 --> 01:56:12,556
"It wouldn't be proper to delay
this matter anymore"

872
01:56:12,799 --> 01:56:15,768
"I hope you will treat this
letter like a telegram"

873
01:56:16,669 --> 01:56:19,638
"Please arrange to send
Ahmed here at the earliest"

874
01:56:20,006 --> 01:56:22,839
"Everything else is fine here;
my folks send you their regards"

875
01:56:23,643 --> 01:56:27,044
"I remain, yours...
- Mukait UI-lah.

876
01:56:27,780 --> 01:56:29,975
I will not listen to any
excuse from Ahmed now.

877
01:56:30,583 --> 01:56:34,110
That's right.
But he's very much here.

878
01:56:34,821 --> 01:56:37,517
Let me tell you, father.
I'm not going there.

879
01:56:38,091 --> 01:56:41,618
This is like...
- This boy is a fool!

880
01:56:42,528 --> 01:56:46,794
I have one foot in the grave and you
have your life ahead of you!

881
01:56:47,600 --> 01:56:52,902
How long will you cling to me?
You don't find such jobs everyday.

882
01:56:53,106 --> 01:56:54,971
Your father is right, son.

883
01:56:55,141 --> 01:57:02,411
In fact, I've heard of people
praying at temples in the cities...

884
01:57:03,116 --> 01:57:05,778
The temple?!
- What's wrong?

885
01:57:06,486 --> 01:57:11,924
Actually, I was headed for the temple
and happened to find his glasses.

886
01:57:12,725 --> 01:57:15,159
That's it! I forgot
where I was going!

887
01:57:15,828 --> 01:57:18,524
But I've remembered it now!

888
01:57:21,634 --> 01:57:25,035
Hey, Veeru... there goes
your horse-cart girl.

889
01:57:30,977 --> 01:57:34,037
Well, Basanti...
you're on foot today.

890
01:57:34,814 --> 01:57:37,214
Has your mare run away
with the cart?

891
01:57:37,784 --> 01:57:44,053
You still don't understand
that no one elopes out here.

892
01:57:44,957 --> 01:57:47,585
My mare is honourably at home
and today being a Monday...

893
01:57:48,127 --> 01:57:53,121
aunt told me that if l pray
to Lord Shiva on every Monday...

894
01:57:53,499 --> 01:57:55,831
I'll get a husband that
the world will be stunned.

895
01:57:56,269 --> 01:58:00,831
I said, okay... I don't intend
to marry a bum anyway.

896
01:58:01,207 --> 01:58:03,937
Okay, then... I must leave.
Praise the Lord!

897
01:58:09,515 --> 01:58:11,540
Praise the Lord!

898
01:58:16,122 --> 01:58:18,147
Praise the Lord!

899
01:58:36,008 --> 01:58:40,206
Lord! There is nothing in the
world that is hidden from You.

900
01:58:40,847 --> 01:58:42,678
You are omniscient, Lord!

901
01:58:43,249 --> 01:58:45,683
I don't say that You have
forgotten it.

902
01:58:46,285 --> 01:58:48,617
But it's always good
to remind You.

903
01:58:48,888 --> 01:58:51,948
Today's a Monday and I have
a small request, Lord.

904
01:58:52,825 --> 01:58:59,162
Look at my hands, rough and rugged
from holding the reins!

905
01:58:59,732 --> 01:59:01,666
And what problems
could You have, Lord?

906
01:59:02,034 --> 01:59:06,562
Get me married into a family where
I will rule like the Queens!

907
01:59:06,906 --> 01:59:08,931
Life's gotta be fun!

908
01:59:10,309 --> 01:59:12,903
I leave the rest to You.

909
01:59:13,613 --> 01:59:15,103
Young lady...

910
01:59:17,750 --> 01:59:19,775
Who spoke?

911
01:59:20,853 --> 01:59:22,878
It is I who has spoken!

912
01:59:23,956 --> 01:59:28,052
Lord! It's You!
This is a miracle!

913
01:59:31,330 --> 01:59:36,563
I have found a match
for you, lady.

914
01:59:36,836 --> 01:59:39,771
In just one Monday?
That's excellent!

915
01:59:40,039 --> 01:59:42,337
You must obviously have
chosen the best!

916
01:59:42,842 --> 01:59:46,141
Could You tell me the name, perhaps?
Or do I come again next week?

917
01:59:46,879 --> 01:59:51,316
I will do as You say, Lord.
- His name is Veeru.

918
01:59:52,051 --> 01:59:57,182
Veeru?! This has to do with my life!
Please don't make haste, Lord!

919
01:59:57,390 --> 01:59:59,620
I wouldn't mind You taking
a few Mondays more.

920
02:00:00,326 --> 02:00:03,659
He's okay to look at;
but he's a bloody smart ass!

921
02:00:04,096 --> 02:00:06,030
Silence, maiden!

922
02:00:06,265 --> 02:00:10,861
I never talk without reason, Lord!
I'll do as You say!

923
02:00:11,337 --> 02:00:18,106
If you don't obey my command, you
will remain a spinster all your life!

924
02:00:18,244 --> 02:00:19,836
Forgive me, Lord!

925
02:00:23,115 --> 02:00:26,380
You will continue to drive the
horse-cart all your life!

926
02:00:27,220 --> 02:00:34,956
I now command you to go and tell
your aunt, in no uncertain terms...

927
02:00:35,361 --> 02:00:39,195
that it is Veeru who will be
your companion for life!

928
02:00:40,099 --> 02:00:45,401
To respect and honour Veeru
therefore shall be your prime duty!

929
02:00:46,339 --> 02:00:51,367
Because, your heavens
lie at his feet!

930
02:00:52,445 --> 02:00:57,007
Should you please him,
I shall be pleased!

931
02:00:57,984 --> 02:01:03,650
And if you irritate him,
I shall be enraged!

932
02:01:04,090 --> 02:01:05,216
Really?

933
02:01:06,158 --> 02:01:08,126
So go to him...

934
02:01:24,944 --> 02:01:26,377
I thought I would...

935
02:01:27,046 --> 02:01:31,312
You thought this village belle
has no brains!

936
02:01:31,884 --> 02:01:34,944
You thought you could fool me!
You think you're smart!

937
02:01:35,421 --> 02:01:38,356
But I could outsmart guys
like you!

938
02:01:38,791 --> 02:01:41,817
Sit here and play God!
I'm going home!

939
02:01:43,763 --> 02:01:45,958
Atleast listen to me!

940
02:02:19,165 --> 02:02:24,102
When Any Beautiful Girl Sulks

941
02:02:24,403 --> 02:02:28,931
She Becomes Even More Beautiful

942
02:02:38,617 --> 02:02:44,156
When The Car Leaves The Station

943
02:02:44,156 --> 02:02:47,990
She Becomes One, Two, Three

944
02:03:12,051 --> 02:03:13,643
Go from here

945
02:03:14,053 --> 02:03:19,423
In Hands Is A Whip,
On Lips Are Curses

946
02:03:27,166 --> 02:03:34,038
Very Tricky Are Horse Carriage
Riding Women

947
02:03:37,009 --> 02:03:43,039
When Any Horse Carriage
Riding Woman Sulks

948
02:03:44,216 --> 02:03:50,086
She Becomes More Lovely

949
02:04:48,013 --> 02:04:55,044
In Hair Is Shade, On Faces Is Sunlight

950
02:05:00,259 --> 02:05:07,688
Very Tasty, Fair One Are Your
Color And Beauty

951
02:05:10,302 --> 02:05:15,205
When A Kite Breaks From lts String

952
02:05:17,877 --> 02:05:21,813
Her Face Becomes Colorful

953
02:05:57,182 --> 02:05:59,309
I've thought of
something today.

954
02:06:00,219 --> 02:06:02,414
You must do that,
once in a while.

955
02:06:03,055 --> 02:06:05,717
I've taken a very
crucial decision today.

956
02:06:06,525 --> 02:06:11,630
I know what your decision is;
you want to marry Basanti.

957
02:06:11,630 --> 02:06:14,258
That's wonderful!
You're a true friend!

958
02:06:14,700 --> 02:06:16,998
Only a friend could
know how I feel!

959
02:06:17,202 --> 02:06:22,504
But I also know that this is your
8th decision to marry this year.

960
02:06:23,342 --> 02:06:24,570
But this is final!

961
02:06:24,710 --> 02:06:27,440
Really? No wonder... you've been
drinking from early this morning.

962
02:06:30,449 --> 02:06:33,043
Will you do something for me?
- What is it?

963
02:06:33,652 --> 02:06:38,112
Go and talk to Basanti's aunt;
make such an impression...

964
02:06:38,390 --> 02:06:40,358
that the old lady is compelled
to propose our marriage!

965
02:06:40,492 --> 02:06:42,255
Why must I do that?

966
02:06:42,461 --> 02:06:44,554
It's the groom's folks who
approach the bride's parents!

967
02:06:45,130 --> 02:06:48,361
Besides, you're the only one
I have in the world, my friend!

968
02:06:49,401 --> 02:06:51,733
It's your wedding, okay?
So go and do this yourself.

969
02:06:52,371 --> 02:06:56,171
Give it a thought...
a cozy home, after marriage!

970
02:06:56,609 --> 02:06:59,169
A home that is yours.
- A loving wife...

971
02:06:59,612 --> 02:07:01,273
Your wife.
- A handful of kids...

972
02:07:01,647 --> 02:07:04,673
All yours, too.
- You're the one they'll call uncle!

973
02:07:05,217 --> 02:07:08,209
They'll forever pester you,
play with you all the time...

974
02:07:08,587 --> 02:07:12,546
and ask you
to tell them a story!

975
02:07:16,328 --> 02:07:19,559
Which means I'm going to play
the maid-servant in your house.

976
02:07:21,500 --> 02:07:23,764
It's clear now!
You are no friend!

977
02:07:24,703 --> 02:07:26,728
To hell with such a...

978
02:07:31,610 --> 02:07:36,309
Acting pricey, aren't you? Because
no one else can do this for me?

979
02:07:38,450 --> 02:07:41,715
Had only my mom been alive,
I'd have settled down in life!

980
02:07:42,488 --> 02:07:44,456
I'd even have had kids!

981
02:07:44,590 --> 02:07:48,583
Had my old man been around, he'd
have celebrated my wedding in style!

982
02:07:48,794 --> 02:07:51,354
Had I brothers and sisters,
they'd have begged the old lady...

983
02:07:51,730 --> 02:07:54,392
but seen to it that
I married Basanti.

984
02:07:54,833 --> 02:07:59,532
But don't you forget! Those without
support, have God on their side!

985
02:08:00,272 --> 02:08:01,705
Lord Almighty!

986
02:08:03,308 --> 02:08:05,276
You're not the friend I knew!

987
02:08:05,511 --> 02:08:08,571
You don't want me to give up crime
and settle down in life!

988
02:08:10,182 --> 02:08:15,245
What had I imagined you to be...
and what you really are!

989
02:08:19,892 --> 02:08:24,693
The bloody clown...
he's forever up to dramatics!

990
02:08:26,465 --> 02:08:29,593
Cut the act! I'll go and talk
it over with the old lady.

991
02:08:30,369 --> 02:08:31,495
Will you, really?!

992
02:08:31,670 --> 02:08:31,704
An unmarried girl at home is
like a burden on the soul, son.

993
02:08:31,704 --> 02:08:38,610
An unmarried girl at home is
like a burden on the soul, son.

994
02:08:38,811 --> 02:08:42,747
I can be at peace, only when
Basanti is married.

995
02:08:43,282 --> 02:08:47,343
You're right. You are indeed
bearing a burden.

996
02:08:47,753 --> 02:08:50,779
But I can't just dump her
in a well, can I?

997
02:08:51,657 --> 02:08:54,922
Please don't mind this,
but I must ask...

998
02:08:55,494 --> 02:09:00,932
about the suitor's family,
his habits and his earnings.

999
02:09:02,000 --> 02:09:07,666
As far as earnings go,
once he is married...

1000
02:09:08,607 --> 02:09:10,802
he will start earning
to fend for them.

1001
02:09:11,243 --> 02:09:13,973
Doesn't he earning anything
at the moment, then?

1002
02:09:14,613 --> 02:09:16,672
Of course, he does!
When did I say that he doesn't?

1003
02:09:16,882 --> 02:09:20,716
It's like this; no one can
win all the time, can he?

1004
02:09:21,820 --> 02:09:24,084
There are times the poor chap
even loses money.

1005
02:09:24,656 --> 02:09:26,556
Loses money?
- That's right...

1006
02:09:26,992 --> 02:09:30,223
but that's gambling, you know.
There's little I can say about it.

1007
02:09:30,696 --> 02:09:33,599
My God! Is he a gambler?

1008
02:09:33,599 --> 02:09:36,659
Not at all, madam!
It's a shame to call him a gambler!

1009
02:09:37,536 --> 02:09:39,936
He's a gem of a person;
decent and straight.

1010
02:09:40,706 --> 02:09:46,076
But when someone is high on liquor,
he can't see things in perspective.

1011
02:09:46,879 --> 02:09:51,077
They force him into gambling.
How's poor Veeru to blame?

1012
02:09:51,250 --> 02:09:58,179
You're right, son. A drinker and
a gambler... and yet, faultless!

1013
02:09:58,290 --> 02:10:03,922
You're misunderstanding my friend.
He's an innocent, young chap.

1014
02:10:04,730 --> 02:10:07,130
Just get him married to Basanti...

1015
02:10:07,766 --> 02:10:10,758
he'll give up drinking
and gambling in no time!

1016
02:10:10,903 --> 02:10:13,269
Don't tell me, son.
I know better.

1017
02:10:13,906 --> 02:10:17,137
Has anyone ever been able to kick
habits like drinking and gambling?

1018
02:10:17,309 --> 02:10:21,803
You don't know Veeru. Believe me,
he's not at all like that.

1019
02:10:22,247 --> 02:10:25,683
Once he's married, he'll stop
visiting the nautch girl. Period!

1020
02:10:25,884 --> 02:10:27,681
His drinking problem will be
solved on its own!

1021
02:10:27,853 --> 02:10:32,688
Good Lord! That's all he lacked!
He even visits brothels, does he?

1022
02:10:33,091 --> 02:10:35,082
So what's wrong with that?

1023
02:10:35,861 --> 02:10:40,230
Even kings and princes have
often patronised dancing-girls!

1024
02:10:41,099 --> 02:10:46,594
I see... but can you tell me which
family your friend hails from?

1025
02:10:46,972 --> 02:10:50,305
We'll let you know that,
the moment we get to know of it!

1026
02:10:50,709 --> 02:10:56,705
I must say one thing, son.
For all your friend's vices...

1027
02:10:56,949 --> 02:11:00,851
you can only praise him!

1028
02:11:01,019 --> 02:11:04,079
I can't help it, aunt.
I'm really soft at heart.

1029
02:11:05,791 --> 02:11:09,194
So, do I take it then that
they will soon be married?

1030
02:11:09,194 --> 02:11:12,630
Married? It's okay even if she
remains a spinster all her life!

1031
02:11:12,931 --> 02:11:15,297
But I will not let Basanti
marry such a man!

1032
02:11:15,701 --> 02:11:17,726
I'm her aunt; not her step-mother!

1033
02:11:19,738 --> 02:11:24,801
It's strange that you refuse,
despite the best of my efforts.

1034
02:11:26,411 --> 02:11:31,178
Poor Veeru. I don't know
how he will deal with this.

1035
02:11:32,150 --> 02:11:32,184
I'll take a jump and die!
Out of my way!

1036
02:11:32,184 --> 02:11:37,747
I'll take a jump and die!
Out of my way!

1037
02:11:38,390 --> 02:11:39,880
Hey, watch it!
What are you doing?

1038
02:11:40,058 --> 02:11:44,825
I'm doing just what every
legendary lover has done!

1039
02:11:45,764 --> 02:11:51,066
They died for their beloveds!

1040
02:11:51,970 --> 02:11:53,995
Suicide!

1041
02:11:57,876 --> 02:11:59,639
Well now... what is suicide?

1042
02:12:00,379 --> 02:12:02,973
When the English die,
they call it suicide.

1043
02:12:03,782 --> 02:12:06,410
But why do the English die?

1044
02:12:07,953 --> 02:12:11,787
What's up, feller? Why do you
want to commit suicide?

1045
02:12:12,024 --> 02:12:16,893
You'd rather not ask!
You'll break into tears!

1046
02:12:17,195 --> 02:12:19,993
It's a very sad story!

1047
02:12:20,299 --> 02:12:25,202
It has emotions, drama
and tragedy!

1048
02:12:26,271 --> 02:12:30,799
You know Basanti, don't you?
I was going to marry her.

1049
02:12:31,443 --> 02:12:36,005
But her wicked aunt has
been an obstacle!

1050
02:12:37,015 --> 02:12:40,143
I can't live in this big,
bad world, anymore!

1051
02:12:40,953 --> 02:12:47,119
I bid you farewell, villagers!
Good-bye!

1052
02:12:50,429 --> 02:12:52,454
Well... what is "good-bye"?

1053
02:12:53,165 --> 02:12:55,759
When the English leave,
it's called "good-bye".

1054
02:12:56,168 --> 02:12:58,728
But where do the English go?

1055
02:12:58,937 --> 02:13:01,997
Hey, villagers! Here I go!

1056
02:13:02,908 --> 02:13:07,174
God Almighty! Here I come!
- Hold it! Wait...!

1057
02:13:07,479 --> 02:13:14,408
What?! Okay, if you insist,
I'll wait for a while.

1058
02:13:15,320 --> 02:13:18,847
Hey... you're a strange friend!
You're sitting here unaffected!

1059
02:13:19,391 --> 02:13:21,416
Why? What's wrong?
- How am I to know?

1060
02:13:21,827 --> 02:13:24,728
Look at your friend!
He's climbed all the way up there!

1061
02:13:26,331 --> 02:13:28,322
You see that, don't you?!

1062
02:13:30,135 --> 02:13:32,330
Yes, I do.
But nothing's going to happen.

1063
02:13:33,071 --> 02:13:35,266
He'll climb down,
when he sobers down.

1064
02:13:36,241 --> 02:13:40,268
I've seen many cruel people.
But not a heartless friend like you!

1065
02:13:41,013 --> 02:13:42,503
Hey, watch out!

1066
02:13:43,415 --> 02:13:47,511
I have no one in the world!
Nor friend, nor buddy...

1067
02:13:48,787 --> 02:13:50,914
So I'm going to end my life!

1068
02:13:51,456 --> 02:13:54,186
But I must warn you, villagers!

1069
02:13:55,060 --> 02:14:01,226
Where a lover ends his life, the
village is wrought with calamities!

1070
02:14:01,833 --> 02:14:03,494
What calamities will
we have to face?

1071
02:14:03,835 --> 02:14:10,502
There will be famine and drought!
Diseases and death!

1072
02:14:10,976 --> 02:14:15,879
And all that only for the sake of
that old hag! That old hag indeed!

1073
02:14:16,014 --> 02:14:17,208
My God!

1074
02:14:17,983 --> 02:14:22,181
You will see for yourselves!
When I die...

1075
02:14:23,155 --> 02:14:28,218
the police will arrive and take
the old hag away to jail!

1076
02:14:29,461 --> 02:14:36,526
In jail, the old hag will
labour on the grindstone...!

1077
02:14:38,303 --> 02:14:40,863
You'd better agree, lady.
Or he'll kill himself!

1078
02:14:41,073 --> 02:14:43,507
But how can I agree, Dinanath?!

1079
02:14:44,276 --> 02:14:49,339
You don't have to beg for anything
from the hag, villagers!

1080
02:14:50,215 --> 02:14:52,240
Nothing can stop me now!

1081
02:14:52,551 --> 02:14:54,576
I will certainly end my life!

1082
02:14:57,456 --> 02:15:00,118
Here goes; one, two, three...

1083
02:15:00,592 --> 02:15:02,253
Please, aunt! Agree to what he says!

1084
02:15:02,627 --> 02:15:05,095
You'd better agree, or do the rounds
of the courts and police stations!

1085
02:15:05,397 --> 02:15:07,422
But I've never been a court
or a police station!

1086
02:15:08,033 --> 02:15:09,500
Then you'd better agree.
- All right.

1087
02:15:10,102 --> 02:15:13,333
Stop that, Veeru!
I agree!

1088
02:15:15,073 --> 02:15:17,439
The old lady has agreed!
Now quietly come down!

1089
02:15:18,577 --> 02:15:21,478
Who wants to marry
the old lady!

1090
02:15:22,047 --> 02:15:26,211
It's Dhanno... I mean,
it's Basanti I want to marry.

1091
02:15:26,585 --> 02:15:30,021
I'm willing to marry you, Veeru!
Come down now!

1092
02:15:30,355 --> 02:15:34,257
Hear that, villagers?

1093
02:15:35,060 --> 02:15:38,120
The old lady is willing...
and so is Basanti!

1094
02:15:38,396 --> 02:15:41,229
So my death has been cancelled!

1095
02:15:41,600 --> 02:15:45,036
I'm coming down, aunt...
my adorable aunt!

1096
02:15:45,504 --> 02:15:47,096
I'm coming down...

1097
02:15:53,078 --> 02:15:55,103
What am I going to do now?!

1098
02:16:14,065 --> 02:16:16,465
So long, father.
- You're leaving, are you?

1099
02:16:16,835 --> 02:16:18,700
Go on... my God protect you.

1100
02:16:18,937 --> 02:16:20,928
Write to me, the moment
you reach there.

1101
02:16:22,040 --> 02:16:26,670
You're a very careless eater;
look after your health, okay?

1102
02:16:27,812 --> 02:16:30,804
As my father, God bless his soul,
used to say...

1103
02:16:31,116 --> 02:16:34,950
in good health lies
true happiness and wealth.

1104
02:16:36,087 --> 02:16:38,749
Let me walk with you for a while.
I'll get myself some air, too.

1105
02:16:39,457 --> 02:16:42,392
It's okay, father. Relax...
I'll go away from here.

1106
02:16:43,461 --> 02:16:47,727
Really? Okay, then...
Let's embrace.

1107
02:16:52,804 --> 02:16:53,038
Hurry up, Junga... I hold
the Queen of clubs.

1108
02:16:53,038 --> 02:16:55,131
Hurry up, Junga... I hold
the Queen of clubs.

1109
02:16:55,907 --> 02:17:00,071
That's okay, Samba. But look there;
the easy prey.

1110
02:17:34,546 --> 02:17:36,537
Chief...
- Yes?

1111
02:17:36,848 --> 02:17:38,873
This boy's from Ramgarh.

1112
02:17:39,718 --> 02:17:42,778
He was on his way to the station,
when we found him.

1113
02:19:12,110 --> 02:19:15,876
Why's there so much
of silence here?

1114
02:19:25,357 --> 02:19:27,587
Imam Saheb...
- Who's that?

1115
02:19:29,160 --> 02:19:34,223
Veeru? Why's there so much
of silence here, son?

1116
02:19:36,334 --> 02:19:38,564
Please come with me.

1117
02:19:39,637 --> 02:19:41,832
Please come...
- What's wrong?

1118
02:19:43,775 --> 02:19:46,835
What's up, son?
Where are you leading me...

1119
02:19:49,047 --> 02:19:50,309
Who's that?

1120
02:19:57,255 --> 02:19:58,347
Ahmed?!

1121
02:20:02,127 --> 02:20:03,617
Ahmed!

1122
02:20:27,252 --> 02:20:30,744
Imam Saheb, I must...

1123
02:20:30,889 --> 02:20:34,017
How will you console him, Thakur?
You're responsible for all this.

1124
02:20:35,360 --> 02:20:36,884
It's true!

1125
02:20:37,962 --> 02:20:43,093
And you villagers had better listen
to this letter from Gabbar, too!

1126
02:20:44,969 --> 02:20:48,735
Addressed to the people of
Ramgarh, it says, "Look at the..."

1127
02:20:49,340 --> 02:20:52,776
"consequences of challenging me
at the Thakur's instigation"

1128
02:20:54,012 --> 02:20:57,038
"Should you folks still
not mend your ways..."

1129
02:20:57,916 --> 02:21:01,079
"death shall perform its ugly dance
in every courtyard of Ramgarh!"

1130
02:21:02,153 --> 02:21:06,419
"Should you care for the lives
of your family and children..."

1131
02:21:07,158 --> 02:21:08,921
"then before sunrise tomorrow..."

1132
02:21:09,294 --> 02:21:14,357
"hand over the Thakur's men
to me, at the old hillock"

1133
02:21:15,099 --> 02:21:17,966
He has signed it off as
"Gabbar Singh, chief of the bandits."

1134
02:21:19,270 --> 02:21:23,297
How could you land us in such
a grave danger, Thakur!

1135
02:21:34,018 --> 02:21:40,389
To lead an honourable life, we will
have to pay a price, Dinanath.

1136
02:21:42,794 --> 02:21:46,286
We can pay the bandits with
food-grains for our lives.

1137
02:21:46,998 --> 02:21:49,228
We can't pay them with
our children's lives!

1138
02:21:49,934 --> 02:21:52,368
We're farmers, after all.
We are not soldiers.

1139
02:21:53,037 --> 02:21:56,268
You are right, Shankar.
We are indeed farmers.

1140
02:21:57,775 --> 02:22:00,403
This has been a country
of farmers for many ages.

1141
02:22:01,813 --> 02:22:04,941
But whenever someone evil has
shown aggressive designs...

1142
02:22:05,483 --> 02:22:10,011
by God, it was farmers who
melted their ploughs into swords!

1143
02:22:11,956 --> 02:22:17,019
It's not the blood of cowards
that flows in our veins! No!

1144
02:22:17,228 --> 02:22:20,720
But how is violence and bloodshed
going to help?

1145
02:22:21,266 --> 02:22:23,291
Non-violence has its place, too.

1146
02:22:24,302 --> 02:22:26,896
I do believe in non-violence.

1147
02:22:27,772 --> 02:22:29,433
But it won't be an
act of non-violence...

1148
02:22:29,807 --> 02:22:31,502
...to grovel before
a wicked and evil man!

1149
02:22:31,910 --> 02:22:34,208
It's nothing but cowardliness!
Plain spinelessness!

1150
02:22:34,846 --> 02:22:37,371
Those who don't bow
are broken down, Thakur!

1151
02:22:38,116 --> 02:22:41,347
This Thakur can neither be made
to bow nor be broken down!

1152
02:22:42,287 --> 02:22:45,085
This Thakur can only die!

1153
02:22:46,357 --> 02:22:50,919
But I will live in dignity,
till as long as I live!

1154
02:22:51,396 --> 02:22:54,490
For how long are you going to live?
And how long will we live either...

1155
02:22:54,899 --> 02:22:56,924
with these guys
around in the village?

1156
02:23:00,271 --> 02:23:03,107
If you think you can save
your children's lives...

1157
02:23:03,107 --> 02:23:05,132
by handing us over
to Gabbar Singh...

1158
02:23:05,410 --> 02:23:12,373
you can very well give us
up to Gabbar. We are willing.

1159
02:23:13,384 --> 02:23:15,545
Yes. We must do
the right thing now.

1160
02:23:16,421 --> 02:23:18,981
We can't bear the burden
of this problem anymore.

1161
02:23:22,827 --> 02:23:25,352
Who's speaking of not
bearing the burden?

1162
02:23:26,998 --> 02:23:30,399
Do you know what is the biggest
burden in the world?

1163
02:23:32,837 --> 02:23:35,431
A father bearing
the bier of his son!

1164
02:23:36,274 --> 02:23:38,469
There can be no bigger burden.

1165
02:23:40,411 --> 02:23:42,811
An old man like me is willing
to bear this burden...

1166
02:23:43,448 --> 02:23:47,544
and you refuse
to combat a problem?

1167
02:23:49,887 --> 02:23:53,948
There's something I very
strongly believe in.

1168
02:23:56,094 --> 02:23:59,586
An honourable death is anyday
better than a life of humiliation.

1169
02:24:01,566 --> 02:24:04,330
It's I, who has lost a son.

1170
02:24:05,870 --> 02:24:09,169
But I'd still want both of them
to stay on in this village.

1171
02:24:10,575 --> 02:24:12,600
I leave the rest to you.

1172
02:24:20,385 --> 02:24:22,410
It's time for my prayers.

1173
02:24:23,921 --> 02:24:27,982
I will ask God today
why He did not give me...

1174
02:24:28,393 --> 02:24:31,419
some more sons to be
sacrificed for the village.

1175
02:24:34,599 --> 02:24:37,966
Will someone please help me
reach the mosque...?

1176
02:26:10,895 --> 02:26:12,886
What's that? A letter?

1177
02:26:13,064 --> 02:26:16,158
Of course, you idiot!
Read it.

1178
02:26:17,101 --> 02:26:21,561
"If you kill one villager, Gabbar,
we will slay four of your men."

1179
02:26:22,974 --> 02:26:26,808
Check out if it's those guys, or
have they dumped someone else here?

1180
02:27:04,115 --> 02:27:10,247
"For every villager you kill, Gabbar,
we will slay four of your men."

1181
02:27:23,167 --> 02:27:25,158
The fun begins now!

1182
02:27:26,571 --> 02:27:31,167
It's ages since I've run into
someone who boasts so much!

1183
02:27:33,277 --> 02:27:35,507
The real fun begins now!

1184
02:27:37,081 --> 02:27:42,917
This game will end with the
lives of these two guys.

1185
02:27:44,255 --> 02:27:47,918
Every family and household in
Ramgarh, will end with this, too!

1186
02:27:55,333 --> 02:27:57,528
Here you are.

1187
02:28:00,004 --> 02:28:01,995
It was really bothering you.

1188
02:28:18,756 --> 02:28:20,781
She's a very unfortunate girl.

1189
02:28:21,559 --> 02:28:24,289
It's almost as if she has
forgotten to speak.

1190
02:28:25,229 --> 02:28:29,689
As for earlier, I'm always reminded
of those days...

1191
02:28:30,801 --> 02:28:33,827
when I first visited her village
with my master.

1192
02:28:34,939 --> 02:28:36,770
It was on the festival
of colours.

1193
02:28:37,275 --> 02:28:39,266
Hey! That's enough!

1194
02:28:39,677 --> 02:28:43,943
It's the festival of colours!
No one can take offense!

1195
02:28:44,849 --> 02:28:47,909
How will I celebrate with your father
if you douse all the colours on me?

1196
02:28:48,252 --> 02:28:50,550
How will you celebrate the festival
with my father in any case?

1197
02:28:50,755 --> 02:28:52,780
He just doesn't know how
to celebrate the festival!

1198
02:28:53,324 --> 02:28:55,554
He's been sitting at home
all day!

1199
02:28:55,927 --> 02:28:59,192
Either he touches the feet
of the elders visiting him...

1200
02:28:59,597 --> 02:29:01,929
or the younger ones touch his
feet as a mark of respect.

1201
02:29:02,633 --> 02:29:06,330
They apply a pinch of colour on
each other's forehead from a plate...

1202
02:29:06,837 --> 02:29:09,362
embrace each other and
that's it! They've celebrated it!

1203
02:29:09,840 --> 02:29:13,276
That's no way of doing it!
It's us, who really celebrate it!

1204
02:29:13,644 --> 02:29:16,306
Really? And how do
you celebrate it?

1205
02:29:17,548 --> 02:29:19,413
You know Paro, don't you?

1206
02:29:19,684 --> 02:29:21,811
Paro?
- Yes! Paro!

1207
02:29:22,520 --> 02:29:27,753
There's a tank in her courtyard.
We've mixed all the colours in it!

1208
02:29:28,025 --> 02:29:29,959
Where folks normally douse
colour on people...

1209
02:29:30,328 --> 02:29:32,762
we dump people
in the colours!

1210
02:29:32,964 --> 02:29:36,900
The moment we spot someone,
he goes straight in the tank!

1211
02:29:38,035 --> 02:29:40,697
I hope you don't have a tank
of colours in your house!

1212
02:29:41,405 --> 02:29:43,805
Or Ramlal and I will find
ourselves neck-deep in it.

1213
02:29:47,011 --> 02:29:48,842
Watch what I do!

1214
02:29:49,280 --> 02:29:51,009
Anyone in, mister?

1215
02:29:51,649 --> 02:29:52,877
Who's that?

1216
02:29:54,452 --> 02:29:56,784
I've scared you again!
- You're crazy!

1217
02:29:57,855 --> 02:29:59,823
The Thakur!
You didn't even tell me!

1218
02:30:00,024 --> 02:30:02,584
Welcome! Greetings of the season!

1219
02:30:04,528 --> 02:30:07,258
What are you standing there for?

1220
02:30:07,565 --> 02:30:10,363
Won't you bring some sweets
for the Thakur?

1221
02:30:10,534 --> 02:30:11,831
Just a moment...

1222
02:30:12,036 --> 02:30:13,970
Must I bring the plate too?
- Which one?

1223
02:30:14,638 --> 02:30:16,629
The one from which you will
take a pinch of colour...

1224
02:30:16,807 --> 02:30:18,798
Sure, go ahead and bring it.

1225
02:30:20,444 --> 02:30:22,275
Please come, Thakur.

1226
02:30:22,913 --> 02:30:26,940
Let's go and sit there...
it's very loud out here.

1227
02:30:28,019 --> 02:30:31,546
So, Ramlal? Is everything fine?
- I'm fine, thank you, sir.

1228
02:30:32,556 --> 02:30:35,423
Well, Thakur? I hope you've
had a nice crop this year.

1229
02:30:35,693 --> 02:30:38,287
Actually, I'm an outsider
in my own house.

1230
02:30:38,729 --> 02:30:41,630
It's Ramlal who knows everything
about my farms.

1231
02:30:42,366 --> 02:30:44,732
It's he who commands things
in our farms.

1232
02:30:45,803 --> 02:30:49,569
Sweets for everyone!

1233
02:30:50,041 --> 02:30:52,009
Open your mouth, uncle!

1234
02:30:53,377 --> 02:30:54,742
That's enough, dear...

1235
02:30:55,346 --> 02:30:57,678
Okay, Mr Ramlal...
open your mouth!

1236
02:30:58,449 --> 02:31:00,518
Give it to me, dear. I'll have it.
- No, sir!

1237
02:31:00,518 --> 02:31:02,918
I will feed you!
- Give it to me, dear.

1238
02:31:03,654 --> 02:31:06,782
She's like your daughter, Ramlal.
Let her feed you.

1239
02:31:07,091 --> 02:31:09,821
He's right. Now open your mouth!

1240
02:31:12,630 --> 02:31:15,599
My God! How could I forget the
plate with the colours?

1241
02:31:17,368 --> 02:31:18,699
She's a very jovial girl.

1242
02:31:18,836 --> 02:31:22,772
You bet! She's always
kicking up a racket!

1243
02:31:23,507 --> 02:31:25,873
Here I come with
the plate of colours!

1244
02:31:26,710 --> 02:31:30,646
Here's the plate of colours for you
to take a pinch out of it!

1245
02:31:30,848 --> 02:31:33,749
I'm leaving!
- Where are you going?

1246
02:31:34,985 --> 02:31:38,921
I'm going to my friends to celebrate!
May I leave?

1247
02:31:40,157 --> 02:31:42,625
Haven't you had enough
of the colours yet?

1248
02:31:44,128 --> 02:31:49,794
It's a festival of colours, uncle...
of all hues!

1249
02:31:50,534 --> 02:31:52,559
How can anyone ever have
enough of the colours?

1250
02:31:52,736 --> 02:31:57,400
Tell me; wouldn't the world be
so dull, without these colours?

1251
02:32:05,716 --> 02:32:08,514
How dull and lifeless her world
has suddenly come to be.

1252
02:32:09,120 --> 02:32:13,420
With her tears having washed away
her bridal-henna...

1253
02:32:13,624 --> 02:32:15,888
what colours can
she look forward to in life?

1254
02:33:43,747 --> 02:33:49,845
I've taken a decision.

1255
02:33:50,754 --> 02:33:53,780
Really? So you've started
taking decisions too?!

1256
02:33:55,693 --> 02:33:59,060
Yes. When you are into it,
I think I'd rather do it too.

1257
02:33:59,797 --> 02:34:01,992
What is that?
- Get married.

1258
02:34:03,934 --> 02:34:05,196
Get married?!

1259
02:34:07,037 --> 02:34:09,139
You want to get married?!

1260
02:34:09,139 --> 02:34:11,164
Yes... I've had enough.

1261
02:34:12,142 --> 02:34:15,202
I've now decided to lead
a straight and simple life.

1262
02:34:16,280 --> 02:34:19,841
In which I have a house of my own,
a wife, many children...

1263
02:34:20,751 --> 02:34:22,820
who will pester you
for stories...

1264
02:34:22,820 --> 02:34:26,119
Hey! That's enough!
Sit down here, will you?

1265
02:34:26,857 --> 02:34:28,882
Sit down here, I say.

1266
02:34:30,995 --> 02:34:35,625
I hope you know that you need
a girl to get married to?

1267
02:34:37,201 --> 02:34:39,226
Have you approved of a girl then?

1268
02:34:40,304 --> 02:34:42,829
Yes, I have.
- Who is she, may I ask?

1269
02:34:48,245 --> 02:34:49,872
That Radha?!

1270
02:34:50,614 --> 02:34:52,980
Are you mad? Don't you know
who she is?

1271
02:34:54,051 --> 02:35:00,615
Now look; even thugs and criminals
are given a second chance in life.

1272
02:35:01,225 --> 02:35:03,216
And then, Radha has done
nothing wrong.

1273
02:35:03,727 --> 02:35:06,025
Has she no right to start
life afresh?

1274
02:35:06,697 --> 02:35:11,725
How can that be? What will society
and community think of it?

1275
02:35:11,935 --> 02:35:17,874
The society and community are
meant to save man from loneliness.

1276
02:35:18,942 --> 02:35:21,137
They're not meant to
isolate someone.

1277
02:35:22,046 --> 02:35:26,312
Besides, must we let Radha suffer
in silence for fear of society?

1278
02:35:29,320 --> 02:35:33,780
How long are we going to live
anyway? We might soon be dead.

1279
02:35:35,192 --> 02:35:38,958
Whose support will she live on?
Whom will she turn to?

1280
02:35:40,297 --> 02:35:43,027
It was because of all this
that I came to you.

1281
02:35:44,301 --> 02:35:47,759
But you are her father.
I leave the decision to you.

1282
02:35:48,205 --> 02:35:50,867
Not at all, Thakur.
She's your daughter now.

1283
02:35:52,643 --> 02:35:55,703
Whatever you decide will be
best for her.

1284
02:35:57,114 --> 02:36:00,845
I'd still want you to
meet Jai at least once.

1285
02:36:01,885 --> 02:36:03,876
I'll send him over
in a couple of days.

1286
02:36:21,071 --> 02:36:23,096
A penny for your thoughts!

1287
02:36:24,875 --> 02:36:26,035
It's nothing.

1288
02:36:26,944 --> 02:36:31,176
I get it! I know what
you're worrying about.

1289
02:36:32,182 --> 02:36:36,642
You're wondering whether your
proposal will come through.

1290
02:36:37,254 --> 02:36:39,245
I suggest you toss again.

1291
02:36:39,957 --> 02:36:43,984
If it's Heads, it's gonna
be okay. Or else... well!

1292
02:36:46,730 --> 02:36:52,828
If everything works out
well, Veeru...

1293
02:36:53,904 --> 02:36:56,304
why don't we settle down here,
in this village?

1294
02:36:56,774 --> 02:36:59,208
There! You've spoken my heart!

1295
02:37:00,110 --> 02:37:02,135
I've been thinking of this, too.

1296
02:37:02,279 --> 02:37:04,747
It's no use being thieves
all our lives.

1297
02:37:04,948 --> 02:37:06,973
We've spent enough time
in the prisons.

1298
02:37:07,351 --> 02:37:10,081
Once we get the money,
let's settle down here.

1299
02:37:10,821 --> 02:37:13,881
We'll buy some land and
turn farmers.

1300
02:37:14,224 --> 02:37:18,923
But we can't use the plough...
how will we be farmers?

1301
02:37:20,798 --> 02:37:25,132
Our vices taught us to wield guns;
our virtues will teach us this.

1302
02:37:25,335 --> 02:37:28,964
You're right. Necessity does
teach a man a lot in life.

1303
02:37:29,406 --> 02:37:31,772
I've already worked out
everything for myself!

1304
02:37:32,176 --> 02:37:33,973
I'll marry the girl
who drives the horse-cart...

1305
02:37:34,178 --> 02:37:37,045
and be the father of a
couple of children in 23 years.

1306
02:37:37,781 --> 02:37:39,339
I've even thought
of the brats' names!

1307
02:37:39,950 --> 02:37:44,114
And when I ask my wife
where the kids are...

1308
02:37:44,321 --> 02:37:45,754
She'll say...

1309
02:37:46,123 --> 02:37:49,854
"They must be with your friend Jai
to listen to his stories"

1310
02:37:52,396 --> 02:37:56,924
Why must you always send your
children to me for stories?

1311
02:37:57,468 --> 02:38:01,063
You know I can't remember
these bloody stories, Jai!

1312
02:38:01,872 --> 02:38:05,899
Stories, my foot! You don't even
remember what happened yesterday.

1313
02:38:06,043 --> 02:38:09,410
Yesterday? Of course I remember
I met Basanti yesterday!

1314
02:38:10,080 --> 02:38:12,742
We've promised to meet
at the lake this morning!

1315
02:38:13,250 --> 02:38:15,946
This morning, huh?
- Yes!

1316
02:38:17,421 --> 02:38:19,355
Here I go!

1317
02:38:38,175 --> 02:38:39,870
Let's go, Dhanno!

1318
02:38:49,052 --> 02:38:53,853
Let's go! It's a question
of my chastity today!

1319
02:39:21,018 --> 02:39:23,418
Go on, Dhanno! Faster!

1320
02:40:01,925 --> 02:40:04,325
Faster, Dhanno! Go for it!

1321
02:42:37,013 --> 02:42:41,848
What do these guys in Ramgarh
feed their daughters with?

1322
02:42:43,720 --> 02:42:48,953
Look at her... she's one hell
of a spicy doll, isn't she?

1323
02:42:50,961 --> 02:42:52,656
Damn spicy, all right!

1324
02:42:53,130 --> 02:42:57,658
Remember how we went to Jamnadas's
daughter's wedding last year, chief?

1325
02:42:58,201 --> 02:42:59,896
She'd given them a terrific
dance performance there.

1326
02:43:00,103 --> 02:43:01,593
Wow!

1327
02:43:03,673 --> 02:43:04,731
She must be a sizzling dancer!

1328
02:43:06,943 --> 02:43:10,276
Show us a couple
of steps, darling.

1329
02:43:11,882 --> 02:43:15,648
Now look, lady... don't you
act too high and mighty!

1330
02:43:16,253 --> 02:43:21,850
Or I'll scratch off this
beautiful skin... all right?

1331
02:43:30,167 --> 02:43:31,930
Wait a minute, darling.

1332
02:43:35,939 --> 02:43:37,600
Tie the bastard!

1333
02:43:45,882 --> 02:43:48,646
You seem to be thick with him,
what say?

1334
02:43:56,726 --> 02:44:01,857
Well, strong man? Mohammad
comes to the mountain, eh?

1335
02:44:02,933 --> 02:44:06,699
You have a scene with
that babe, do you?

1336
02:44:07,204 --> 02:44:12,574
You bastard! I've yet to see
a creep like you!

1337
02:44:13,310 --> 02:44:15,301
You won't get to see one either.

1338
02:44:18,682 --> 02:44:21,207
Because your life is
now going to end.

1339
02:44:22,285 --> 02:44:24,310
The bastard...
- No!

1340
02:44:35,932 --> 02:44:38,594
Like a house on fire, eh?

1341
02:44:44,174 --> 02:44:46,734
You're pretty thick, aren't you?

1342
02:44:48,078 --> 02:44:52,947
Pick up your gun, Samba!

1343
02:44:56,152 --> 02:44:58,620
And aim your gun at this cur!

1344
02:45:02,726 --> 02:45:04,751
Now listen to me, darling.

1345
02:45:05,095 --> 02:45:10,727
If you wish to save your lover,
show us some dance.

1346
02:45:10,967 --> 02:45:15,904
No! Don't you dare dance
before this dogs, Basanti!

1347
02:45:22,212 --> 02:45:26,649
Delay this any longer, and we'll
blow your lover's head apart!

1348
02:45:28,118 --> 02:45:31,645
There's another thing
I must tell you, darling.

1349
02:45:32,722 --> 02:45:36,818
That man will breathe,
only till you continue to dance.

1350
02:45:38,194 --> 02:45:42,221
That gun will go off, the
moment your feet stop moving.

1351
02:46:28,111 --> 02:46:34,880
Yes, As Long As I Have Life, Oh Lover

1352
02:46:35,418 --> 02:46:39,320
I Will Dance

1353
02:47:30,840 --> 02:47:35,004
Love Never Dies

1354
02:47:35,111 --> 02:47:38,569
It Doesn't Even Fear Death

1355
02:47:51,127 --> 02:47:55,188
We Will Be Robbed, Ruined,
And We Will Die

1356
02:47:55,398 --> 02:48:00,563
But Our Story Will Stay Alive

1357
02:48:49,586 --> 02:48:53,323
If My Anklet Breaks, So What?

1358
02:48:53,323 --> 02:48:57,282
If My Legs Become Wounded, So What?

1359
02:49:09,372 --> 02:49:13,343
Having Given My Heart, Taken A Heart,
Fallen In Love, So

1360
02:49:13,343 --> 02:49:18,542
I Have To Give Love's Test

1361
02:50:28,451 --> 02:50:32,755
These Eyes Cannot Be Cast Down

1362
02:50:32,755 --> 02:50:36,247
This Voice Cannot Be Stopped

1363
02:50:51,708 --> 02:50:55,804
I Will Speak, I Will Bear Pain,
Why Should I Stay Silent?

1364
02:50:55,979 --> 02:51:01,383
I Am Out Of Control But
I Am Not Speechless

1365
02:51:45,361 --> 02:51:48,262
If anyone dare moves,
he's gonna be dead meat!

1366
02:51:51,668 --> 02:51:55,434
Gabbar Singh! Ask your men
to drop their guns!

1367
02:52:00,510 --> 02:52:01,807
Go on

1368
02:53:23,526 --> 02:53:25,756
Go after them! Go on!

1369
02:53:26,763 --> 02:53:29,254
And don't return empty-handed,
you bastards!

1370
02:53:31,067 --> 02:53:32,227
Hurry up!

1371
02:55:04,927 --> 02:55:07,259
Jai! Are you all right?
- Yes, I'm okay.

1372
02:55:10,533 --> 02:55:13,991
The three of us can't escape
on a single horse, Veeru.

1373
02:55:14,604 --> 02:55:18,335
Take Basanti away to the village
and return soon.

1374
02:55:18,908 --> 02:55:21,433
And bring lots of ammunition
when you return.

1375
02:55:24,480 --> 02:55:28,109
No! I will stay here!
Take Basanti and leave quickly!

1376
02:55:29,252 --> 02:55:32,847
Listen to me, Veeru!
Take Basanti away! I'll stay here.

1377
02:55:33,122 --> 02:55:35,420
No, Jai! I can't leave you alone.

1378
02:55:36,192 --> 02:55:38,217
One of us will have to go, Veeru.

1379
02:55:38,494 --> 02:55:41,292
Or else, we'll soon
run out of bullets.

1380
02:55:42,198 --> 02:55:45,258
Well, all right.
Let's toss instead.

1381
02:55:46,369 --> 02:55:49,065
If it's Heads, I stay back.
If it's Tails, you hold fort.

1382
02:55:53,075 --> 02:55:54,303
I win!

1383
02:55:58,714 --> 02:56:00,909
But how can you be...
- No more arguments, Veeru!

1384
02:56:01,217 --> 02:56:04,015
Leave your gun and bullets behind.
And take Basanti out quickly! Go on!

1385
02:56:10,760 --> 02:56:13,354
I somehow don't feel like
leaving you alone, Jai.

1386
02:56:14,230 --> 02:56:16,892
Take care, okay?
- Sure.

1387
03:00:14,336 --> 03:00:16,304
There's just one bullet!

1388
03:01:23,873 --> 03:01:27,707
Are you okay, Jai?!
- Yes... I'm okay.

1389
03:01:29,812 --> 03:01:32,872
I've killed every
single bastard before...

1390
03:01:35,651 --> 03:01:38,085
Don't worry, Jai!
Just don't be scared!

1391
03:01:39,154 --> 03:01:42,180
Why must I be scared when
you're with me, Veeru?

1392
03:01:43,292 --> 03:01:46,557
Let's return to our village!
Everything will be all right!

1393
03:01:46,829 --> 03:01:49,821
My game is up, Veeru.

1394
03:01:50,132 --> 03:01:52,225
It's all over...
- No!

1395
03:01:52,868 --> 03:01:55,860
No, Jai! Don't say such things!

1396
03:01:56,939 --> 03:02:00,568
But I have no regrets, Veeru.

1397
03:02:01,210 --> 03:02:05,169
I have lived for my friend...
and am dying before him!

1398
03:02:06,015 --> 03:02:09,007
But there is something
I'm leaving unfinished, Veeru.

1399
03:02:09,818 --> 03:02:11,809
I won't be able to tell
stories to your children.

1400
03:02:12,054 --> 03:02:14,955
You're going to be all right, Jai!
Nothing will happen to you!

1401
03:02:15,257 --> 03:02:20,854
But you must tell your children
tales of our friendship and exploits.

1402
03:02:21,931 --> 03:02:24,297
You won't forget that, will you?
- What nonsense are you talking?!

1403
03:02:30,205 --> 03:02:31,900
Look there, Veeru...

1404
03:02:38,180 --> 03:02:40,705
There's yet another
incomplete story, Veeru.

1405
03:02:41,817 --> 03:02:44,843
What had I dreamed of;
and what has come to be?

1406
03:02:46,055 --> 03:02:51,083
No, Jai!
You can't leave me like this!

1407
03:02:55,264 --> 03:02:56,356
No!

1408
03:02:57,399 --> 03:03:01,096
No, Jai! Please don't!

1409
03:03:03,739 --> 03:03:07,835
No, Jai!
You can't do this to me!

1410
03:03:59,628 --> 03:04:04,463
What you have done?

1411
03:04:04,633 --> 03:04:08,569
You betrayed me

1412
03:04:09,438 --> 03:04:14,432
and broke your promise

1413
03:04:16,912 --> 03:04:21,246
You walked away

1414
03:04:21,450 --> 03:04:33,385
leaving me behind lonely

1415
03:04:33,729 --> 03:04:37,187
you moved on

1416
03:04:39,601 --> 03:04:43,765
you've changed my friend

1417
03:04:46,542 --> 03:04:50,842
and broke our friendship

1418
03:04:52,681 --> 03:05:06,789
We Will Not Break This Friendship

1419
03:05:08,697 --> 03:05:20,541
I May Break My Strength,
But I Will Not Leave Your Side

1420
03:05:47,302 --> 03:05:54,037
Jai! You have cheated me
to save my life?

1421
03:05:59,915 --> 03:06:02,975
I swear upon the blood
that you have shed!

1422
03:06:03,252 --> 03:06:08,315
I will pick and choose each
one of them, and give them death!

1423
03:06:09,224 --> 03:06:12,455
Gabbar Singh!
I'm coming after you!

1424
03:07:15,057 --> 03:07:18,151
Gabbar! Come out in the open!

1425
03:07:19,294 --> 03:07:21,660
Face me like a man,
you bastard!

1426
03:07:22,331 --> 03:07:26,461
I've come to avenge every drop
of blood that my friend has shed!

1427
03:07:27,502 --> 03:07:30,437
You can't escape death today!

1428
03:09:07,936 --> 03:09:10,564
Hand him over to me, Veeru.

1429
03:09:11,039 --> 03:09:15,840
No, Thakur! I'm not going to
let this bastard live anymore!

1430
03:09:16,411 --> 03:09:19,903
Don't forget your promise, Veeru!
- I don't remember anything!

1431
03:09:20,549 --> 03:09:24,986
All I know is that this bastard's
men have killed my friend!

1432
03:09:25,787 --> 03:09:28,085
And I'm going to have
his blood for that!

1433
03:09:28,557 --> 03:09:32,049
It was that very friend of yours
who had made a promise to me.

1434
03:09:34,396 --> 03:09:36,523
Leave him alone.

1435
03:09:46,742 --> 03:09:53,147
I wish it was I who had made the
promise; I'd have broken it today!

1436
03:09:54,449 --> 03:09:57,509
But it was my friend
who gave you his word.

1437
03:09:58,053 --> 03:09:59,111
So...

1438
03:10:45,567 --> 03:10:52,439
You can't fight me, Thakur!
I've already cut your arms!

1439
03:10:53,875 --> 03:10:58,938
One uses his feet, not his hands,
to crush the snake, Gabbar!

1440
03:11:01,750 --> 03:11:04,082
My feet are enough
to deal with you!

1441
03:11:26,708 --> 03:11:29,199
Your arms are full of
strength, aren't they?

1442
03:12:27,903 --> 03:12:32,274
Gabbar! Give your hands to me!

1443
03:12:32,274 --> 03:12:33,605
No!

1444
03:12:33,909 --> 03:12:36,002
Give me this hand, Gabbar!

1445
03:12:36,745 --> 03:12:37,837
No!

1446
03:13:56,925 --> 03:13:57,914
Thakur...

1447
03:14:00,028 --> 03:14:01,655
Leave him alone.

1448
03:14:04,232 --> 03:14:07,099
To punish the criminal
is the duty of the law.

1449
03:14:08,403 --> 03:14:11,668
The law wants Gabbar...

1450
03:14:12,307 --> 03:14:13,740
alive...

1451
03:14:15,410 --> 03:14:16,843
or dead.

1452
03:14:17,045 --> 03:14:21,004
Have your emotions become more
important than your duty and the law?

1453
03:14:24,386 --> 03:14:27,219
Do law and justice no longer merit
the same status in your esteem...?

1454
03:14:34,262 --> 03:14:36,730
I know what you have been through.

1455
03:14:37,365 --> 03:14:40,857
But don't forget,
you have been a police officer...

1456
03:14:41,136 --> 03:14:42,933
who's still an example
for others.

1457
03:16:23,037 --> 03:16:25,232
Well, Thakur...
I must leave now.

1458
03:16:30,345 --> 03:16:34,441
I know I can't share your grief.
But I do understand.

